The company operates through five segments: Printing, Trading and Logistics, Property Development and Investments, Solar Photovoltaic, and Financial Services. It also trades in electronic products and devices, rubber products, paper products, and oil and chemical products; and provides marketing services. In addition, the company offers finance leasing and money lending services; logistics and supply chain management services; and asset management services, as well as invests in equity securities, funds, and bonds. Further, it develops and invests in real estate properties; and manufactures and sells solar control equipment, monocrystalline silicon wafers, polycrystalline silicones, solar cells, coated glasses, rare metals, solar modules, and silicon materials and related products. Additionally, the company provides food, commercial, and accommodation services; and produces and sells turbines, transformers, torque converters, and related products. The company was formerly known as Huajun Holdings Limited and changed its name to Huajun International Group Limited in July 2018. The company was founded in 1964 and is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong. Huajun International Group Limited is a subsidiary of Huajun International Limited.

CIAM Group Limited operates as an investment arm of FDG Electric Vehicles Limited. CIAM Group Limited, an investment holding company, provides private equity investments and fund management services in mainland China. It also involves in property development activities. CIAM Group Limited was formerly known as E2-Capital (Holdings) Limited. CIAM Group Limited is based in Central, Hong Kong, and is considered a Red Chip company due to its listing on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange.

China Ever Grand Financial Leasing Group Co., Ltd., an investment holding company, provides finance lease and related consulting services in the People's Republic of China and Hong Kong. The company operates through Financial Leasing, Terminal and Logistics Services, Investment, and Others segments. It also offers financial lease consulting and other financing services; loading and discharging, and storage services; and lease of terminal facilities and equipment. In addition, the company is involved in investments in securities and properties; and engages in money lending business. Further, it is involved in research and development, manufacture, and sale of food additives, food ingredients, and nutritional enhancers. The company was formerly known as PME Group Limited and changed its name to China Ever Grand Financial Leasing Group Co., Ltd. in February 2016. China Ever Grand Financial Leasing Group Co., Ltd. is headquartered in Wan Chai, Hong Kong.
longName: China Ever Grand Financial Leasing Group Co., Ltd.

longBusinessSummary: Softpower International Limited, an investment holding company, trades in construction materials in Hong Kong, Macau, and Mainland China. The company engages in the wholesale, retail, warehouse, and logistics of pipes, fittings, and other related accessories to the contractors, designers, consultants, and government agencies. Its products include copper tubes, stainless steel and steel pipes, etc. The company was formerly known as China Pipe Group Limited and changed its name to Softpower International Limited in December 2015. Softpower International Limited was founded in 1949 and is headquartered in Tsim Sha Tsui, Hong Kong.

Kiu Hung International Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, manufactures and trades in toys and gifts. It operates through five segments: Manufacturing and Trading of Toys and Gifts Items, Exploration of Natural Resources, Fruit Plantation, Leisure, and Culture. The company also owns the exploration rights of Bayanhushuo Coal Field and Guerbanhada Coal Mine located in Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region. In addition, it invests in fruit plantation, outbound tourism, tea and wine products related, and cultural items businesses. Further, the company provides management services; trades in gifts, toys, and flags and garden products; holds and invests in properties; invests in securities; and offers corporate finance services. It operates in the People's Republic of China, the United States, Canada, Spain, Italy, France, the United Kingdom, the Middle East, South America, and Southeast Asia. The company was formerly known as Kiu Hung Energy Holdings Limited and changed its name to Kiu Hung International Holdings Limited in December 2014. Kiu Hung International Holdings Limited was founded in 1991 and is headquartered in Wan Chai, Hong Kong.

Edvantage Group Holdings Limited operates higher education institutions in the People's Republic of China. It also operates a vocational education institution in Australia. The company was founded in 2003 and is headquartered in Guangzhou, China.

China Medical & HealthCare Group Limited, an investment holding company, primarily operates hospitals. It operates through six segments: Healthcare, Eldercare, Property Development, Property Investment, Financial Services, and Securities Trading and Investments. The company is also involved in the property development of independent living units; and project management of health campus with a focus on elderly care and retirement community comprising elderly nursing homes, service apartments, and independent living units, as well as a shopping mall, retail shops, and club hall facilities. In addition, it develops and sells properties and land; leases residential and office properties; and provides money lending, financial and strategic investment, and healthcare services. Further, the company is involved in the medical equipment and related supplies. Additionally, it invests and trades in securities. The company operates in the People's Republic of China and Hong Kong. It is also involved in the trading of securities listed in overseas exchange. The company was formerly known as COL Capital Limited and changed its name to China Medical & HealthCare Group Limited in February 2016. The company is headquartered in Wanchai, Hong Kong.

China Gas Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, operates as a gas operator and service provider in the People's Republic of China and Hong Kong. It operates in Sales of Piped Gas, Gas Connection, Engineering Design and Construction, Sales of LPG, Value-Added Services, and Zhongyu Gas segments. The company invests in, constructs, and operates city and town gas pipeline infrastructure facilities, gas terminals, storage and transportation facilities, and gas logistics systems; transmits natural gas and liquefied petroleum gas (LPG) to residential, industrial, and commercial customers; constructs and operates compressed natural gas/liquefied natural gas refilling stations; and develops and applies technologies related to natural gas and LPG in China. It is also involved in the investment in petrochemical facilities of storage and transportation, and fundamental facilities of pier; sale of raw chemical materials and construction materials; producing and storing LPG and chemical products, as well as propane and butane; CBM business; exploration and production of coal bed methane; and gas station construction, management, and consultancy services. In addition, the company offers treasury, management, consultancy, goods transportation, goods transportation agency, technical advisory, IT consulting, and communication systems and computer software sale services. Further, it is involved in the development and investment in clean energy; distribution of city gas and natural gas for vehicle use; construction of long distance natural gas pipeline; and trading of heaters and boilers. Additionally, the company engages in the research, development, wholesale, retail, installation, and maintenance of household equipment, electric appliances, kitchen appliances, and others. As of March 31, 2019, it served 12,407 industrial customers and 199,637 commercial customers; and 29,678,157 residential customers. China Gas Holdings Limited is headquartered in Wan Chai, Hong Kong.

Chinney Alliance Group Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the trading of plastic and chemical products, and building related contracting activities. It operates through five segments: Plastic and Chemical Products, Building Related Contracting Services, Building Construction, Foundation Piling and Ground Investigation, and Others. The company offers building related contracting services, including engineering contracting services in the air-conditioning industry and maintenance services; superstructure construction work services; and foundation piling, and drilling and site investigation services. It is also involved in contracting of building aluminum works; the distribution and installation of aviation systems and other hi-tech products, as well as mechanical, electrical, and building supplies; trading of electrical, air-conditioning, and other building supply products; and maintenance of air-conditioning, electrical generators, water pumps, and fire prevention and fighting systems. In addition, the company trades in building decoration materials, generators, and electrical and mechanical engineering materials and equipment; and holds properties and investments. Further, it is involved in the treasury functions; basement construction works; agency trading of industrial products; equipment and machinery leasing; construction material testing; design, installation, repair, and maintenance of electrical and mechanical systems; trading of electrical installation products; provision of management services; and sale and installation of air-conditioning systems. It primarily serves public and private sectors in Hong Kong, Mainland China, Macau, and Singapore. The company is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong.

China Petroleum & Chemical Corporation, an energy and chemical company, engages in oil and gas, and chemical operations in the People's Republic of China. It operates through five segments: Exploration and Production, Refining, Marketing and Distribution, Chemicals, and Corporate and Others. The company explores for and develops oil fields; produces crude oil and natural gas; processes and purifies crude oil; and manufactures and sells petroleum products. It also owns and operates oil depots and service stations; and distributes and sells refined petroleum products, including gasoline and diesel through wholesale and retail sales networks. In addition, the company manufactures and sells petrochemical and derivative petrochemical products; and other chemical products, such as basic organic chemicals, synthetic resins, synthetic fiber monomers and polymers, synthetic fibers, synthetic rubber, and chemical fertilizers. Further, it is involved in the pipeline transportation and sale of petroleum and natural gas; production, sale, storage, and transportation of refinery and coal chemical products; import and export of petroleum, natural gas, petroleum products, petrochemical and chemical products, and other commodities and technologies; research, development, and application of technologies and information; production and sale of catalyst products, lubricant base oil, polyester chips and fibers, plastics, and intermediate petrochemical products; research, development, production, and sale of ethylene and downstream by-products; and coal chemical industry investment management activities. The company was founded in 2000 and is headquartered in Beijing, the People's Republic of China. China Petroleum & Chemical Corporation is a subsidiary of China Petrochemical Corporation.

Leeport (Holdings) Limited, an investment holding company, imports and distributes equipment and precision tools for the manufacturing industry primarily in the People's Republic of China, Hong Kong, and internationally. Its products include metal cutting machines; metal forming machinery; measuring instruments; cutting tools; professional and machine tools and accessories; electronic equipment; and rapid prototype equipment. The company is also involved in the trading, installation, and provision of after-sales service of metalworking machinery, measuring instruments, cutting tools, and electronic equipment. In addition, it offers product design, prototype fabrication, and part manufacturing services. Further, the company holds properties. The company was founded in 1967 and is headquartered in Kwai Chung, Hong Kong. Leeport (Holdings) Limited is a subsidiary of Peak Power Technology Limited.

China Tontine Wines Group Limited, an investment holding company, produces and sells grape wine products. The company offers sweet wines and dry wines under the Tongtian, Tongtian Hong, and TONTINE labels. It also produces and sells brandy, white wines, and ice wines, as well as processes grape juices. In addition, China Tontine Wines Group Limited is involved in the grapes plantation and wholesale and retail of wine products; and offers administrative services. It sells its products through distributors in 20 provinces, 3 autonomous regions, and 4 municipal cities in the People's Republic of China. The company was founded in 2001 and is headquartered in Tonghua, the People's Republic of China. China Tontine Wines Group Limited is a subsidiary of Up Mount International Limited.

China Railway Group Limited, together with its subsidiaries, operates as an integrated construction company in the People's Republic of China and other Asian countries. Its Infrastructure Construction segment constructs railways, highways, bridges, tunnels, metropolitan railways, buildings, irrigation works, hydroelectricity projects, ports, docks, airports, and other municipal works. The company's Survey, Design and Consulting Services segment provides survey, design, consulting, research and development, feasibility study, and compliance certification services to infrastructure construction projects. Its Engineering Equipment and Component Manufacturing segment designs, researches and develops, manufactures, and sells turnouts, bridge steel structures, and other railway related equipment, engineering machinery, and materials. The company's Property Development segment develops, sells, and manages residential and commercial properties. Its Other Businesses segment is involved in mining, financial, service concession arrangements operation, merchandise trading, and other ancillary businesses. China Railway Group Limited was founded in 1950 and is based in Beijing, China.

Mei Ah Entertainment Group Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the television business in the People's Republic of China and internationally. The company is also involved in film exhibition; film rights licensing and sub-licensing; theatre operations; concert performance and events organization; mobile games applications and video online; artiste management; and property investment businesses, as well as the sale and distribution of films and programs in audio visual product format. It also produces films and tele-features. The company was founded in 1984 and is headquartered in Tseung Kwan O, Hong Kong.

Beijing Enterprises Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in piped gas, brewery, water and environmental, solid waste treatment, and other businesses primarily in Mainland China. Its Piped Gas Operation segment distributes and sells piped natural gas; provides natural gas transmission services, as well as repair and maintenance services; surveys and plots underground construction projects; and constructs and installs gas pipelines and related equipment. The company's Brewery Operation segment produces, distributes, and sells brewery products. Its Water and Environmental segment constructs sewage and water treatment plants and other infrastructural facilities; provides construction services for renovation projects; offers sewage treatment, and water treatment and distribution services, as well as consultancy services; and licenses technical know-how related to sewage treatment. The company's Solid Waste Treatment segment is involved in the construction and operation of waste incineration plants; waste treatment; sale of electricity; generation of heat and stream from waste incineration. Its Corporate and Others segment offers consultation and property investment services. Beijing Enterprises Holdings Limited was founded in 1997 and is based in Wan Chai, Hong Kong. Beijing Enterprises Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Beijing Enterprises Group (BVI) Company Limited.

Glorious Sun Enterprises Limited, an investment holding company, retails, trades, and exports casual wear apparel. The company operates through four segments: Retail, Wholesale, Franchise and Others; Export Operations; Financial Investments; and Interior Decoration and Renovation. The Retail, Wholesale, Franchise and Others segment engages in retail and wholesale operations, as well as franchise sale activities under Jeanswest Brand in casual wear and apparel domain. The Export Operations segment exports apparel. The Financial Investments segment is involved in the treasury management. The Interior Decoration and Renovation Business segment engages in the interior decoration and renovation businesses, as well as sale of furniture. As at 31 December 2018, the company operated 11 Jeanswest branded stores in Hong Kong. The company has operations in Mainland China, Australia, New Zealand, Canada, Hong Kong, the United States, and internationally. Glorious Sun Enterprises Limited is headquartered in Kowloon Bay, Hong Kong.

Smartac Group China Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides online to offline (O2O), integrated digital marketing, and e-commerce solutions in the People's Republic of China. The company offers its O2O services to social customer relationship management (CRM) platforms; big data management for retail sectors; and maintenance service for voice recording system, call center system, and social CRM platforms. It also provides digital advertisements and promotion articles for customers through WeChat official account; and WeChat Pay payment service. In addition, the company provides marketing strategy and management of operation of online shop on e-commerce platform; communication system installation and system integration services; software development services; and advertising, networking, and IT related services, as well as trades in goods. The company was formerly known as Sino Dragon New Energy Holdings Limited and changed its name to Smartac Group China Holdings Limited in May 2014. Smartac Group China Holdings Limited was founded in 1977 and is headquartered in Causeway Bay, Hong Kong.

Hing Lee (HK) Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, designs, manufactures, trades in, sells, markets, and exports home furniture. It primarily offers wood-based furniture, sofa, and mattresses for bedroom, living room, dining room, and home office use. The company markets its products under the Aomax, Mogou, Johnston, and Oriant brand names. It also licenses its own brands, product designs, and trademarks. The company distributes its products in approximately 600 outlets. It operates in the People's Republic of China, rest of Asia, Europe, the United States, and internationally. The company was formerly known as HingLi Home Concepts Ltd. and changed its name to Hing Lee (HK) Holdings Limited in November 2008. Hing Lee (HK) Holdings Limited was incorporated in 2004 and is headquartered in Shatin, Hong Kong.

Power Financial Group Limited, an investment holding company, primarily engages in financial services business in Hong Kong and the People's Republic of China. It operates through Financial Services, Money Lending, and Assets Investment segments. The company offers securities broking, placing, underwriting, corporate finance advisory, and loan financing services, as well as involved in holding of properties. It also invests in listed and unlisted equity securities, debt securities, and options and investment funds; and engages in the personnel management activities. The company was formerly known as Jun Yang Financial Holdings Limited and changed its name to Power Financial Group Limited in March 2018. Power Financial Group Limited is headquartered in Sheung Wan, Hong Kong.

Oriental Watch Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, trades in watches in Hong Kong, Macau, Taiwan, and the People's Republic of China. It primarily offers various Swiss brands comprising Rolex, Tudor, Piaget, Vacheron Constantin, Audemars Piguet, IWC, Jaeger-LeCoultre, Girard Perregaux, Longines, Omega, etc. The company is also involved in the property holding activities, as well as provision of watch repair and maintenance services. As of March 31, 2019, it operated through 61 retail and wholesale points, which included associate retail stores in the Greater China region. Oriental Watch Holdings Limited was founded in 1961 and is based in Central, Hong Kong.

Innovative Pharmaceutical Biotech Limited, an investment holding company, provides genetic testing services in the People's Republic of China and Hong Kong. The company also engages in the trading of beauty equipment and products; distribution of bio-industrial products; and securities investment activities. In addition, it is involved in the research, development, and commercialization of oral insulin products; and engages in the healthcare management business. The company was formerly known as United Gene High-Tech Group Limited and changed its name to Innovative Pharmaceutical Biotech Limited in September 2015. Innovative Pharmaceutical Biotech Limited is headquartered in Sheung Wan, Hong Kong.

Cogobuy Group operates as an e-commerce company serving the electronics manufacturing industry in the People's Republic of China and Hong Kong. It sells integrated circuits and other electronic components comprising microcontrollers/processors, sensors and converters, signal and interface products, amplifiers, filters, optoelectronic devices, resistors, inductors, discrete devices, connectors, switches, relays, circuit protection devices, development tools and systems, multimedia ICs, and dedicated and motor control ICs, as well as FPGA/CPLD, DSP, memory, wireless and RF, power management, capacitance, timer, and clock products. The company offers its products through its e-commerce platform, cogobuy.com, which includes a direct sales platform, as well as through an online marketplace, and a team of technical consultants and professional sales representatives. It also provides media communication and collaboration platforms and solutions; supply chain financing services; and develops e-commerce software technology. In addition, the company develops and sells electronic communication products; operates the INGDAN.com platform; and holds Internet content provider license. It serves electronics manufacturers, including small and medium enterprise, and blue-chip customers. The company was founded in 2000 and is headquartered in Shenzhen, the People's Republic of China. Cogobuy Group is a subsidiary of Envision Global Investments Limited.

Wanjia Group Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in pharmaceutical wholesale and distribution business in the People's Republic of China. It also offers hemodialysis treatment and consultancy services. The company sells its products to hospitals and healthcare institutions; distributors; and companies operating pharmaceutical retail chain stores, independent pharmacies, outpatient departments of community hospitals, healthcare service stations, and clinics in Fujian province. Wanjia Group Holdings Limited was founded in 2004 and is headquartered in North Point, Hong Kong.

Starlite Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in printing and manufacturing packaging materials, labels, and paper products in the People's Republic of China, the United States, South East Asia, Europe, and internationally. The company offers molded pulp products for various products, such as drink or food trays, bowls and plates, clamshell containers, egg cartons, shipping materials, and point of purchase packaging products; provides roll and sheet form labels on various substrates, including paper, plastic films, and others; and prints children's and novelty books, and board games comprising pop-up books, board games, puzzles, and book kits. It also provides packaging products for household appliances, toys and games, greeting cards, consumer electronics, food and beverages, luxury, pharmaceuticals, and personal care products; blister, window box, and APET box packaging products; and luxury packaging products. In addition, the company offers electronic products, such as sound modules, light sensors, and electric motors for paper printing; and e-business services through its Website GreenTaNet.com. Further, it distributes team green products; provides management services; manufactures and trades in machinery and automated equipment; trades in paper products and packaging materials; and holds trade and service marks. The company was founded in 1970 and is headquartered in San Po Kong, Hong Kong.

Yau Lee Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the construction business in Hong Kong, Macau, Singapore, and Mainland China. It operates in Construction, Electrical and Mechanical Installation, Building Materials Supply, Property Investment and Development, and Hotel Operations segments. The company contracts for various private developers and government institutions; and constructs resorts, hotels, and residential buildings. It also provides architectural and engineering, theme painting, curtain wall and steel work, plumbing and drainage, GRC, GRG, GRP, and construction IT services, as well as pre-fabricated products. In addition, the company offers construction IT services, including software development, project management, system development, and integration and IT outsourcing services. Further, it trades in construction and building materials; provides a range of import/export services, such as applying for certificate of origin and 3C, cargo insurance agency, prepayment of import/export tax and charges, etc.; and invests in, develops, and operates residential, commercial, and industrial properties. Additionally, the company offers building information modeling, and other virtual design and construction; electrical, mechanical, ventilation and air conditioning, fire, plumbing, and environmental engineering; energy optimization and environmental protection; water treatment; project management and consultancy; hotel management; patent licensing; and training services. It is also involved in the design, installation, maintenance, renovation, and fitting-out of buildings; environmental protection related software and programming activities; development of computer software; manufacture and sale of precast products and building materials; distribution of books; and trading of environmental technology products. The company was founded in 1958 and is headquartered in Kowloon Bay, Hong Kong.

Yip's Chemical Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, produces and sells petrochemical products in the People's Republic of China. It operates through four segments: Solvents, Coatings, Inks, and Lubricants. The Solvents segment produces industrial organic solvents, such as ethyl acetate, normal butyl acetate, propyl acetate, mixed butyl acetate, ethanol, and butyl acrylate for use in coatings, tannery, medicine, and adhesives industries. The Coatings segment provides architectural coatings, including inner and outer emulsion wall paints and wood paints for the household paints market; industrial coatings comprising coatings for furniture and plastic products, as well as anti-corrosive coatings; and resins, which include alkyd, acrylic, UV, amino, and water-based resins, as well as PU hardeners. This segment primarily offers its products under the Camel, Aquapro, and VIVA brands. The Inks segment provides plastic printing inks and paper printing inks for use in food, drinks and gift packaging, and paper printing applications under the Bauhinia Variegata brand name. The Lubricants segment offers automotive and industrial lubricants, including engine oils, antifreezes, system coolants, brake fluids, greases, gear oils, automatic transmission fluids, hydraulic oils, turbine oils, heat conducting oils, slideway oils, compressor oils, and circulating oils under the Hercules brand name. It also provides specialty lubricants under the Pacoil brand name to the metal processing, automobiles, home appliances, electronics, steel, toys, power generation, cement, textiles, foundry, plastics, chemicals, paper making, glass, and wires and cables industries. The company also invests in properties; trades in coatings, solvents, resins, inks, and lubricants; and offers treasury services. The company was formerly known as Hang Cheung Hong. Yip's Chemical Holdings Limited was founded in 1971 and is headquartered in Wanchai, Hong Kong.

SOHO China Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the real estate development, and property leasing and management activities in China. The company operates in two segments, Properties Development and Properties Investment. It invests in, develops, rents, and sells various properties, as well as operates serviced apartments. The company was founded in 1995 and is headquartered in Beijing, China.

Lam Soon (Hong Kong) Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the manufacture, trading, and processing of edible oil, flour products, and home care products in Hong Kong, the People's Republic of China, and Macau. The company operates through two segments, Food and Home Care. The Food segment manufactures and sells a range of food products comprising flour, edible oils, and vegetable fats for the catering industries and consumers. The Home Care segment manufactures and distributes household cleaning products, such as liquid dishwashing detergents, laundry powders, liquid laundry detergents, fabric softeners, floor cleaners, and industrial marble cleansers. It markets its products under the Knife, Red Lantern, Soon, AXE, Labour, Procleanic, Golden Statue, American Roses, and Crown, as well as Golden Double Peach brands. The company is also involved in the trading of flour, edible oils, cleaning, commodity derivatives, and agency products; provision of trucks rental, warehousing and logistics, information technology, and trustee services; and property and trademark holding businesses. In addition, it provides silo facilities. The company was founded in 1961 and is headquartered in Tai Po, Hong Kong. Lam Soon (Hong Kong) Limited is a subsidiary of Guoline International Limited.

China Shandong Hi-Speed Financial Group Limited, an investment holding company, provides various financial services in Hong Kong and the People's Republic of China. The company operates through four segments: Investments in Securities, Money Lending, Financial Leasing, and Financial Technology. The Investments in Securities segment purchases and sells securities and derivatives; holds equity and debt investments; and offers investments related advisory services. The Money Lending segment provides money lending and advisory services. The Financial Leasing segment primarily is involved in the provision of direct financial leasing and advisory services, as well as operation of an asset trading platform. The Financial Technology segment offers online investment and technology enabled lending services; and online new media services. It also provides corporate, business factoring, securities brokerage, and asset management services; and issues guaranteed bonds. China Shandong Hi-Speed Financial Group Limited has a strategic cooperation agreement with Shangdong Hi-Speed Hubei Development Co., Ltd. The company was formerly known as China Innovative Finance Group Limited and changed its name to China Shandong Hi-Speed Financial Group Limited in October 2017. China Shandong Hi-Speed Financial Group Limited is headquartered in Wanchai, Hong Kong.
longName: China Shandong Hi-Speed Financial Group Limited

longBusinessSummary: South China Holdings Company Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the manufacture and trading of toys, property investment and development, and agriculture and forestry businesses. Its Trading and Manufacturing segment is involved in the manufacture and trading of merchandises, including toys, footwear, and leather products. The company's Property Investment and Development segment engages in the property investment and development activities. This segment has a property portfolio with total floor area of approximately 580,000 square meters in Mainland China; and 26,000 square meters in Hong Kong. Its Agriculture and Forestry segment is involved in the cultivation of fruit trees and crops; rearing of livestock and aquatic products; and forestation and sale of relevant agricultural produces. The company also manufactures and trades in electronic products; and manufactures and sells leather chemical and sports products. In addition, it invests in, develops, and manages properties. Further, the company is involved in the woods plantation business. It has operations in the People's Republic of China, the United States, Europe, Japan, and internationally. The company was formerly known as South China (China) Limited and changed its name to South China Holdings Company Limited in June 2015. South China Holdings Company Limited was founded in 1976 and is based in Central, Hong Kong.

Bank of Jinzhou Co., Ltd. provides various banking products and services in the People's Republic of China. The company operates through Corporate Banking, Retail Banking, Treasury Business, and Other Business segments. The Corporate Banking segment provides deposits, loans, settlement and clearing, and other products and services. The Retail Banking segment offers deposits, bank and credit cards, personal and collateral loans, and personal wealth management services. The Treasury Business segment provides money market placements, investments and repurchasing, and foreign exchange transactions services. The company also provides payment and finance leasing, and other banking services. As of June 30, 2019, it operated through a network of 15 branches, 195 sub-branches, 3 micro sub-branches, 7 mini/community sub-branches, and 1 specialized institution located primarily in Beijing, Tianjin, Harbin, and Liaoning. The company was formerly known as Jinzhou City Commercial Bank Co., Ltd. and changed its name to Bank of Jinzhou Co., Ltd. in December 2015. Bank of Jinzhou Co., Ltd. was founded in 1997 and is headquartered in Jinzhou, the People's Republic of China.

Tse Sui Luen Jewellery (International) Limited, an investment holding company, manufactures, sells, and markets jewelry products in Hong Kong, Macau, Mainland China, Malaysia, and other countries. The company operates through Retail Business, Wholesale Business, and Other Businesses segments. It is also involved in the retail and wholesale of jewelry; property holding and investment businesses; and management and administrative services, as well as logistic and supply chain management activities. The company was founded in 1971 and is based in Hunghom, Hong Kong. Tse Sui Luen Jewellery (International) Limited is a subsidiary of Partner Logistics Limited.

Founder Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the software development, system integration, and information products distribution activities in Hong Kong, Mainland China, and internationally. It is also involved in the properties holding business. The company is headquartered in Tsuen Wan, Hong Kong.

Huayi Tencent Entertainment Company Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the entertainment and media business in the People's Republic of China and internationally. It operates in two segments, Entertainment and Media Businesses; and Offline Healthcare and Wellness Services. The company produces films, animations, and TV dramas, as well as invests in international entertainment companies. It is also involved in the licensing of films and TV dramas; advertising agency activities; and the provision of offline health and wellness services through operation of wellness center. In addition, the company offers Internet and information technology services; and engages in the hotel management business. The company was formerly known as China Jiuhao Health Industry Corporation Limited and changed its name to Huayi Tencent Entertainment Company Limited in May 2016. Huayi Tencent Entertainment Company Limited was incorporated in 2002 and is based in Hong Kong, Hong Kong.

Fountain Set (Holdings) Limited, an investment holding company, produces and sells knitted fabrics and garments in Hong Kong, the People's Republic of China, Taiwan, Korea, Sri Lanka, the United States, Europe, and internationally. It is involved in fabric knitting, dyeing, printing, finishing, and garment manufacturing activities. The company also offers yarn dyed fabrics, printed fabrics, and dyed yarns and fabrics; and garments, including men's wear, women's wear, children's wear, and sportswear. In addition, it engages in trading yarns, dyestuffs, and chemicals, as well as garments and fabrics; and the heating supply activities. The company was founded in 1969 and is headquartered in Kwai Chung, Hong Kong. Fountain Set (Holdings) Limited is a subsidiary of Chinatex Yieldfull Investments Co., Ltd.

Vietnam Manufacturing and Export Processing (Holdings) Limited, an investment holding company, manufactures and sells scooters and cub motorbikes, and related spare parts and engines in Vietnam, Malaysia, the Philippines, Singapore, Indonesia, Taiwan, Thailand, and other countries. The company offers motorbikes under the SYM and SANDA brands. It also manufactures molds for making die-cast and forged metal parts; and provides motorbike maintenance services. As of December 31, 2018, its distribution network comprised approximately 213 SYM authorized stores owned by dealers in Vietnam. The company was founded in 1992 and is headquartered in Bien Hoa, Vietnam. Vietnam Manufacturing and Export Processing (Holdings) Limited is a subsidiary of SY International Ltd.
longName: Vietnam Manufacturing and Export Processing (Holdings) Limited

longBusinessSummary: Hong Kong Economic Times Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, operates as a diversified multi-media company primarily in Hong Kong. It provides content and services in finance, property, lifestyle, human resources, and education business domains in a range of media platforms. The company operates through four segments: Media; Financial News Agency, Information, and Solutions; Recruitment Advertising and Training; and Lifestyle Platforms. The Media segment engages in the printing and publication of newspapers, magazines, periodicals, and books, as well as advertising and circulation activities. The Financial News Agency, Information, and Solutions segment provides electronic financial and property market information and related solutions; and information subscription services, solutions, and other related maintenance services. The Recruitment Advertising and Training segment offers recruitment advertising and training services; and placement of recruitment advertisements, and enrolment for professional training services. The Lifestyle Platforms segment operates digital platforms in food, travel, health, and other lifestyle focus. The company also provides equities and derivatives trading solutions, and funds market database and solutions to the professional market; and operates computer software research and development center. Hong Kong Economic Times Holdings Limited was founded in 1988 and is headquartered in North Point, Hong Kong.
longName: Hong Kong Economic Times Holdings Limited

longBusinessSummary: Minth Group Limited, an investment holding company, designs, develops, manufactures, processes, and sells automobile body parts and molds of passenger cars in the People's Republic of China, the United States, Japan, Thailand, Germany, Mexico, and internationally. The company also manufactures, develops, and sells batteries and motor systems for electric vehicles, as well as optical parts, metal molds, automation machines, software, and production lines; manufactures buses, modified cars, and electric vehicles; develops and manages real estate properties; and offers bookkeeping services. In addition, it engages in import and export trading, logistics, and technology import activities. Minth Group Limited was incorporated in 2005 and is headquartered in Ningbo, the People's Republic of China.

One Media Group Limited, an investment holding company, engages in magazine publishing and digital media businesses in Hong Kong, Taiwan, and Mainland China. The company publishes Ming Pao Weekly, an entertainment, celebrity, and fashion magazine; Ming's, a monthly magazine covering fashion, beauty, luxuries, and arts categories; TopGear Hong Kong, an automobile magazine; TopGear China, an automotive magazine; TopGear Taiwan, a monthly automobile magazine; MING WATCH and MING WATCH CHINA watch magazines; and Ming Watch Plus that provides watch market trends and in-depth coverage of international watch events. It also operates Hihoku, an interactive entertainment portal. In addition, the company is involved in magazines advertising, media operation, trademark licensing, artiste and events management, and music production and distribution activities. One Media Group Limited was incorporated in 2005 and is headquartered in Chai Wan, Hong Kong. One Media Group Limited is a subsidiary of Comwell Investment Limited.

Oriental Explorer Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the property investment and securities trading activities in Hong Kong. The company operates in two segments, Property Investment, and Trading and Investment. Its investment properties primarily comprise office, industrial, and residential units. The company is also involved in the trade of securities; provision of management services; and securities investment business. The company is headquartered in Wong Chuk Hang, Hong Kong. Oriental Explorer Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Limitless Investment Limited.

Greater China Financial Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the industrial property development, general trading, securities brokerage, insurance brokerage, asset management, and loan financing operations in Hong Kong and the People's Republic of China. The company's General Trading segment engages in trading Moutai, a distilled Chinese liquor; and other Chinese liquors. Its Industrial Property Development segment operates a warehouse. The company's Securities Brokerage segment offers securities related services, including securities brokerage, securities trading, margin financing, and placement services. Its Insurance Brokerage segment provides tailor-made financial solutions to its clients; advisory services related to insurance products; and general insurance and mandatory provident fund retirement benefit schemes, as well as linked long term products. The company's Asset Management segment offers asset management services. Its Loan Financing segment provides financing guarantee, loan financing, financing consultancy, and loan referral services. Greater China Financial Holdings Limited also provides commercial factoring services. The company was formerly known as Greater China Holdings Limited and changed its name to Greater China Financial Holdings Limited in December 2015. Greater China Financial Holdings Limited is headquartered in Causeway Bay, Hong Kong.

Pacific Century Premium Developments Limited and its subsidiaries develop and manage property and infrastructure projects in the Asia-Pacific region. It also invests in residential and office buildings and properties; and provides professional property management, facilities management, asset management, and administrative services. In addition, the company offers leasing and financing, property sale agency, and travel agency services, as well as engages in the provision of trademark registrant, hotel management, and ski operation services. The company was incorporated in 1998 and is based in Hong Kong, Hong Kong. Pacific Century Premium Developments Limited is a subsidiary of PCCW Limited.

North Mining Shares Company Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the exploitation, exploration, and trading of mineral resources in the People's Republic of China and internationally. It operates through four segments: Mining Operation, Property Management Operation, Chemical Trading Operation, and Security Technologies Operation. The company has exploitation rights in the molybdenum mine located at Xi Ban Cha Gou, Huanglongpu Village, Shimen Town, Luonan County, Shaanxi Province, as well as a potassium feldspar mine located in Shaanxi Province. It is also involved in the provision of management service to commercial premises; manufactures and sells chemical products; and engages in the research, development, and sale of face recognition technology and intelligent video analysis technology and application, as well as is involved in the sale of molybdenum concentrates. The company was incorporated in 1995 and is headquartered in Wanchai, Hong Kong. North Mining Shares Company Limited is a subsidiary of China Wan Tai Group Limited.

Boyaa Interactive International Limited, an investment holding company, develops and operates online card and board games in the People's Republic of China and internationally. Its Web-based and mobile games include board games; and casual shooting, casual virtual-pet-raising, 8-Ball Pool, and Mahjong games. As of December 31, 2018, the company had a portfolio of 79 online games in 17 versions of languages. It also provides advisory services relating to online game applications. Boyaa Interactive International Limited was founded in 2004 and is headquartered in Shenzhen, the People's Republic of China.

New Universe Environmental Group Limited, an investment holding company, primarily provides environmental waste treatment and disposal services in the People's Republic of China. It provides general and hazardous industrial waste treatment and management services for various chemical related industries; and regulated medical waste treatment and management services for hospitals and clinics, as well as chemical tank truck cleansing services. The company is also involved in the operation of solid waste landfill, which handles general industrial waste and environmentally friendly post-incineration substances; provision of environmental industrial sewage and sludge treatment, and facility services in an eco-plating zone; and provision of environmental technical consultancy and engineering, and management services. In addition, it provides environmental plating sewage treatment services in an eco-plating specialized zone; invests in plastic materials dyeing business; and holds land and buildings. The company was formerly known as New Universe International Group Limited and changed its name to New Universe Environmental Group Limited in May 2016. The company was founded in 1996 and is headquartered in Kowloon Bay, Hong Kong.

IRICO Group New Energy Company Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the solar photovoltaic, new materials, trading, and other businesses in the People's Republic of China and internationally. It researches, develops, produces, and sells solar photovoltaic glasses, solar cells and modules, and solar cell modules and related products; luminous materials, and lithium battery anode materials and related products of flat panel display; and photovoltaic glass upstream quartz sand. The company also constructs and operates solar power stations. In addition, it is involved in the mining exploration activities; production and sale of inorganic nonmetallic materials and products; and trading of solar modules and other related accessories. The company was formerly known as IRICO Group Electronics Company Limited and changed its name to IRICO Group New Energy Company Limited in January 2016. The company was founded in 2004 and is headquartered in Xianyang, the People's Republic of China. IRICO Group New Energy Company Limited is a subsidiary of IRICO Group Corporation Limited.
longName: IRICO Group New Energy Company Limited

longBusinessSummary: KuangChi Science Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the research and development, manufacture, and sale of future technology businesses in the People's Republic of China, Hong Kong, New Zealand, and Canada. It offers provision for in-depth space services and other innovative technology business, and administrative services, as well as trades chips. The company was formerly known as Climax International Company Limited and changed its name to KuangChi Science Limited in September 2014. KuangChi Science Limited is headquartered in Causeway Bay, Hong Kong. KuangChi Science Limited is a subsidiary of New Horizon Wireless Technology Limited.

Dah Sing Financial Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides banking, insurance, financial, and other related services in the People's Republic of China. The company operates through Personal Banking, Commercial Banking, Treasury, Overseas Banking, and Insurance segments. The Personal Banking segment accepts various deposits from individual customers; and provides residential mortgage loans, personal loans, overdrafts, vehicle financing, and credit card services, as well as insurance sales and investment services. The Commercial Banking segment accepts various deposits; and offers loans and working capital financing to commercial, industrial, and institutional customers, as well as trade financing services. The Treasury segment provides foreign exchange services; cash management services for deposit taking and lending; and interest rate risk management services. It also manages investment in securities. The Overseas Banking segment offers personal and commercial banking products and services. The Insurance Business segment is involved in the insurance and pension fund management business. The company also provides insurance agency, nominee, and securities dealing services; and invest in properties. The company was formerly known as Fivetech Investments Limited and changed its name to Dah Sing Financial Holdings Limited in July 1987. Dah Sing Financial Holdings Limited was incorporated in 1987 and is based in Wan Chai, Hong Kong.

Hifood Group Holdings Co., Limited, an investment holding company, designs, manufactures, exports, and sells fine jewelry and related products in the Americas, Mainland China, Russia, rest of Asia, rest of Europe, and internationally. It offers a range of fine jewelry products in karat gold, including rings, earrings, pendants, necklaces, bracelets, bangles, cufflinks, brooches, and anklets. The company offers its jewelry products to wholesalers and retailers. It is also involved in the provision of car rental, as well as management services. The company was formerly known as KTL International Holdings Group Limited and changed its name to Hifood Group Holdings Co., Limited in October 2017. Hifood Group Holdings Co., Limited was incorporated in 2014 and is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong. Hifood Group Holdings Co., Limited is a subsidiary of HNA Aviation Investment Holding Company Ltd.

Sincere Watch (Hong Kong) Limited, an investment holding company, distributes branded luxury watches, timepieces, and accessories in Hong Kong, Macau, Taiwan, Korea, and the People's Republic of China. It operates through two segments, Watch Distribution and Dining Business, and Property Investment segments. The company primarily offers Franck Muller watches and accessories. It offers its products under the de Grisogono, CVSTOS, Pierre Kunz, European Company Watch, and Backes & Strauss brands. The company also engages in the dining business and property investment activities. It operates a distribution network of 50 retail points of sales and 12 boutiques. The company was founded in 1954 and is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong.

CIMC-TianDa Holdings Company Limited, an investment holding company, manufactures and sells airport equipment in the People's Republic of China, rest of Asia, North America, Europe, the Middle East, Africa, South America, and Oceania. It operates through four segments: Passengers Boarding Bridge and Automated Parking System, Ground Support Equipment, Logistics System Business, Fire Engines and Fire Prevention and Fighting Equipment. It manufactures and sells passenger boarding bridges for connecting airport terminals to commercial aircraft, as well as automated vehicle parking systems, such as vertical lifting parking systems, aisle stacking parking systems, vertical and horizontal carriage parking systems, and lift-only parking systems; and manufactures and repairs airport group support equipment comprising airport apron buses, aircraft catering vehicles, cargo loaders, and other specialised vehicles. The company also offers engineering and computer software solutions for baggage, cargos, and materials handling and warehousing systems; and produces and sells fire engines, and fire prevention and fighting equipment. In addition, it offers maintenance and other specialised business services for airport and harbour equipment, as well as infrastructural engineering and maintenance services; sells and distributes passenger boarding bridge and ground support equipment, modern logistics automation system, and high speed sorting systems; supplies and maintains airport logistics systems and equipment; provides sale and technical services of automatic parking system and equipment, mechanical products, metal structural parts, self-produced products, and agent products; and develops and sale of air conditioning equipment. The company is headquartered in Wan Chai, Hong Kong. CIMC-TianDa Holdings Company Limited is a subsidiary of China International Marine Containers (Hong Kong) Limited.

Chigo Holding Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the design, development, manufacture, and sale of residential and commercial air-conditioning products. It also provides air-conditioner parts and components, compressors, and copper products. The company offers its products principally under the CHIGO and HYUNDAI brands through independent regional distributors and household appliances retail chain operators. Chigo Holding Limited offers its products primarily in the People's Republic of China, rest of Asia, the Americas, Africa, Europe, and Oceania. The company was founded in 1994 and is headquartered in Foshan, China. Chigo Holding Limited is a subsidiary of Chigo Group Holding Limited.

Hung Hing Printing Group Limited, an investment holding company engages in the book and package printing, consumer product packaging, and corrugated box and paper trading in the People's Republic of China, Hong Kong, Europe, the United States, and internationally. It produces folding cartons and packaging for toys, cosmetics, and other consumer products, as well as conventional and children's novelty books; prints and produces cards and social stationery items, including diaries, gift sets and bags, and greetings cards; and children's and conventional books. The company also offers novelty items consisting of pop-ups, paper mechanisms, pull tabs, novelty additions, or reactive inks; luxury packaging comprising chocolate boxes, cosmetics, fine bone china, and spirits; printed corrugate cartons, flat packs, POS, and POP; prepress services comprising film, and color separation and proof production services for packaging, books, magazines, posters, and other paper products; and paper trading services, as well as operates BELUGA, a boutique digital service provider. In addition, it engages in the supply of corrugated boxes for toy, food and beverage, electronics, and household product industries; production and color printing of paper products; trade of paper and corrugated carton boxes; and printing and manufacturing of paper cartons, as well as provision of selling and purchasing agency services. Hung Hing Printing Group Limited was founded in 1950 and is headquartered in Tai Po, Hong Kong.

GCL New Energy Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, develops, constructs, operates, and manages solar power plants in the People's Republic of China, Japan, the United States, and internationally. As of June 30, 2019, it owned and operated 212 solar power plants with an aggregate installed capacity of 7,039 megawatts. The company was formerly known as Same Time Holdings Limited and changed its name to GCL New Energy Holdings Limited in May 2014. GCL New Energy Holdings Limited was founded in 1982 and is based in Kowloon, Hong Kong. GCL New Energy Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Elite Time Global Limited.

Tianda Pharmaceuticals Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the research and development, production, and sale of pharmaceutical, biotechnology, and healthcare products in Mainland China, Hong Kong, and Australia. Its product range includes Chinese and western medicines and biochemical drugs, etc., such as cardio-cerebrovascular drugs, pediatric drugs, anti-flu and respiratory system drugs, anti-infection drugs, detoxification agents, and other pharmaceutical products; and health care products comprising bone health, heart health, immune booster, nutritional oil, vitamin and mineral, women's nutrition, wellbeing, personal care, and honey products. The company offers its health care products under the Herb Valley brand name. It also engages in sale and wholesale of Chinese herbal medicines, traditional Chinese medicine decoction pieces and Chinese medicines; and property holding business. The company was formerly known as Tianda Holdings Limited and changed its name to Tianda Pharmaceuticals Limited in September 2012. The company is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong. Tianda Pharmaceuticals Limited is a subsidiary of Tianda Group Limited.

New City Development Group Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the property development and investment activities in the People's Republic of China and Hong Kong. It also trades in buses; and offers general management services. The company was formerly known as New City (China) Development Limited and changed its name to New City Development Group Limited in May 2012. New City Development Group Limited was incorporated in 1998 and is based in Kwun Tong, Hong Kong. New City Development Group Limited is a subsidiary of Junyi Investments Limited.

Tristate Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, designs and manufactures garments in the People's Republic of China, Canada, the United States, and the United Kingdom. The company offers sportswear, military uniforms, authentic outdoor products, womenswear, and work wear under the C.P. Company, EFM, Cissonne, and HASKI brand names. It also engages in the branded product distribution, retail, and trading. In addition, the company offers sales liaison, general administrative and supporting, factory facilities leasing, nominee and secretarial, technical, and design and customer support services. Further, it is involved in trademark holding and licensing, as well as general trading and marketing, and product design and development activities. The company was founded in 1937 and is headquartered in Kwai Chung, Hong Kong. Tristate Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Silver Tree Holdings Inc.

Midland IC&I Limited, an investment holding company, provides property agency services for commercial and industrial properties, and shops in Hong Kong. It is also involved in the property investment, surveying, and money lending activities. The company is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong.

Sihuan Pharmaceutical Holdings Group Ltd., an investment holding company, engages in the research and development, manufacture, and sale of pharmaceutical products in the People's Republic of China. The company offers cardio-cerebral vascular system, central nervous system, metabolism, anti-infective, oncology, and digestive drugs. It also engages in the marketing of pharmaceutical products; manufacture of pharmaceutical materials; project preparation for the manufacture of pharmaceutical products; sale of medical appliances; promotion of technology and consulting services; and construction of medical projects, as well as provision of information support, research and development, business and development, and general hospital and hospital management services. In addition, the company provides import and export trade services; and markets aesthetic medicines. Additionally, it invests in property; constructs environmental protection projects; and wholesales chemical raw materials. The company was founded in 2001 and is based in Wanchai, Hong Kong. Sihuan Pharmaceutical Holdings Group Ltd. is a subsidiary of Plenty Gold Enterprises Limited.

China Overseas Nuoxin International Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, designs, manufactures, and sells electrical haircare and healthcare products, and other small household electrical appliances. The company offers hair dryers, straighteners, curling tongs, and hot air stylers, as well as hair rollers. It also provides contract processing services. The company sells its products through brand owners and importers to beauty supply retailers and wholesalers, chain stores, mass merchandisers, warehouse clubs, and grocery stores, as well as through catalogues. China Overseas Nuoxin International Holdings Limited offers its products in Asia, Europe, North and South America, Africa, and Australia. The company was formerly known as Kenford Group Holdings Limited and changed its name to China Overseas Nuoxin International Holdings Limited in May 2019. China Overseas Nuoxin International Holdings Limited was founded in 1984 and is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong.
longName: China Overseas Nuoxin International Holdings Limited

longBusinessSummary: Futong Technology Development Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides enterprise information technology (IT) infrastructure, cloud computing, and intelligent digitalized application products and services in the People's Republic of China. It also distributes traditional enterprise-grade IT products; and offers system integration services. The company was founded in 1996 and is headquartered in Beijing, the People's Republic of China. Futong Technology Development Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of China Group Associates Limited.

United Energy Group Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the investment and operation of upstream oil, natural gas, and other energy related businesses in Pakistan and Singapore. The company explores for and produces crude oil and natural gas. As of December 31, 2018, its net proven reserves consisted of 95.3 million barrels of oil equivalent. United Energy Group Limited is headquartered in Admiralty, Hong Kong.

Greatview Aseptic Packaging Company Limited, an investment holding company, manufactures, distributes, and sells paper packaging products and filling machines to dairy and non-carbonated soft drink producers in the People's Republic of China and internationally. The company sells its aseptic packaging materials under the GREATVIEW trademark, which includes Greatview Brick, Greatview Pillow, Greatview Crown, Greatview Octagon, and Greatview Blank-Fed. It also provides filling machines, spare parts, technical services, and rubber and plastic films. In addition, the company is involved in the research and development of multi-layer food packaging materials. Greatview Aseptic Packaging Company Limited was founded in 2001 and is headquartered in Beijing, the People's Republic of China.

Capxon International Electronic Company Limited, an investment holding company, manufactures and sells aluminum foils and aluminum electrolytic capacitors. It operates through Capacitors and Aluminum Foils segments. The company is also involved in trading activities, as well as in the manufacture and sale of equipment. Its products are used in consumer electronics, industrial control systems, renewable energy facilities, automation, medical services, vehicles, lighting, air conditioners, communication, smart devices, and other fields. The company has operations in the People's Republic of China, Taiwan, other Asian countries, Europe, the United States, and Africa. Capxon International Electronic Company Limited was founded in 1980 and is headquartered in Wanchai, Hong Kong. Capxon International Electronic Company Limited is a subsidiary of Value Management Holding Limited.

CMMB Vision Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the convergent mobile multimedia broadcasting (CMMB) and printed circuit board (PCB) trading activities in the United States and Taiwan. It operates through CMMB Business and Trading Business segments. The company delivers digital mobile television (TV) and multimedia contents through terrestrial and satellite networks directly to mobile and wireless devices, such as smartphones, tablets, pocket TVs, laptops, automobile digital receivers, and personal media players. It also engages in the free-to-air digital TV broadcasting activities; and procurement and distribution of PCB materials. The company was formerly known as Global Flex Holdings Limited and changed its name to CMMB Vision Holdings Limited in May 2010. CMMB Vision Holdings Limited is based in Hong Kong, Hong Kong.

New Silkroad Culturaltainment Limited, an investment holding company, produces and distributes wine and Chinese baijiu in the People's Republic of China, South Korea, Canada, and Australia. The company offers its products under the YuQuan brand name. It also engages in the operation of an Internet P2P financing platform through mobile application. In addition, the company develops and operates real estate; operates resort and cultural tourism business; and operates casino gaming business under the brand of MegaLuck Casino. Further, it is involved in the procurement and distribution of grapes. The company was formerly known as JLF Investment Company Limited and changed its name to New Silkroad Culturaltainment Limited in July 2015. The company is headquartered in Causeway Bay, Hong Kong.

Hao Tian Development Group Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the financial services, money lending, rental of construction machinery, property investment, and health care businesses in Hong Kong, Macau, the United Kingdom, and the Peoples Republic of China. It provides property mortgage, personal, and unsecured loans to individuals, corporates, and high net worth clients; commodities, futures, and securities brokerage services; asset management, wealth management, and financing services; and transportation services, as well as rents and trades in construction machinery and spare parts. The company invests in and leases real estate properties; retails men and women apparels; sells construction materials; and offers management services. In addition, it is involved in the cultivation and sale of camellia oleifera; development, application, and transfer of agricultural technology; and forest economic investment and development. The company was formerly known as Hao Tian Resources Group Limited and changed its name to Hao Tian Development Group Limited in October 2013. The company was incorporated in 2005 and is based in Wanchai, Hong Kong. Hao Tian Development Group Limited is a subsidiary of Asia Link Capital Investment Holdings Limited.

Central Development Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the design, manufacture, and wholesale of fine jewelry products primarily in the People's Republic of China. The company also manufactures and sells solar cooling intelligent technology products using thermal cooling-stored pipes; sells solar photovoltaic modules and components; and provides energy efficiency analysis and technology enhancement advisory services on solar energy projects. Central Development Holdings Limited offers its jewelry products to jewelry distributors and retailers. The company was formerly known as Zhong Fa Zhan Holdings Limited and changed its name to Central Development Holdings Limited in October 2019. The company is headquartered in Wanchai, Hong Kong. Central Development Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Resources Rich Capital Limited.

China Dynamics (Holdings) Limited, an investment holding company, engages in manufacturing electric vehicles primarily in the People's Republic of China, Hong Kong, and Chile. It operates through Development of Electric Vehicles, Mining, and Metals and Minerals Trading segments. The company is involved in the manufacture and trading of electric buses and motor vehicles, and batteries; development of new energy technology and products; and mining, trading, and sale of metals and mineral resources. It also provides management and computer maintenance services; trades in computer hardware and software; processes and trades in copper ores; and develops software, and energy saving and environmental protection products. The company was formerly known as Sinocop Resources (Holdings) Limited and changed its name to China Dynamics (Holdings) Limited in May 2014. China Dynamics (Holdings) Limited is headquartered in Wanchai, Hong Kong.

CIL Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, distributes server storage, multi-media, and communication products in Hong Kong. The company also distributes rice cookers and household electrical appliances in the People's Republic of China, Southeast Asia, the Middle East, Africa, and South America. In addition, it engages in money lending operations in Hong Kong. Further, the company purchases and sells securities, and holds equity investments; organizes concerts in Hong Kong and Macau; and provides corporate services. CIL Holdings Limited is headquartered in Cheung Sha Wan, Hong Kong.

HKR International Limited, an investment holding company, invests in, develops, and manages real estate properties in Hong Kong, Mainland China, Japan, and South East Asia. It operates in five segments: Property Development, Property Investment, Services Provided, Hotel Operations, and Healthcare. The company primarily develops and manages residential, commercial, and industrial properties, as well as leisure projects. It also owns, operates, and manages hotels; and a healthcare service network, including chronic disease management and integrated medical centers, Chinese medicine centers, dental clinics, a center for the diagnosis and treatment of cancer, and multi-specialty outpatient centers. In addition, the company offers transportation services in Discovery Bay, including ferry, land transport, and tunnel operations; operates clubs; and invests in securities. Further, it provides cancer treatment and diagnostic imaging, commercial leasing agency, property agency, bus and garage, dental health and care, and project and estate management services; corporate consultancy services to healthcare operating units; and financial services to first hand purchasers of properties in Discovery Bay, as well as trades in medical and dental equipment and supplies. Additionally, the company engages in the operation of a shipyard and road tunnel; and diabetes and endocrine disorders clinics, as well as acts as an estate manager and principal lessee of communication network in Discovery Bay. HKR International Limited was founded in 1977 and is based in Central, Hong Kong.

Sandmartin International Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the manufacture and trading of satellite TV equipment products and other electronic goods. It operates through Media Entertainment Platform Related Products; Other Multimedia Products; Integration of Signal System and Traffic Communication Network; Satellite TV Equipment and Antenna Products; and Satellite TV Broadcasting segments. The company manufactures and trades in media entertainment platform related products used for satellite products equipment; components of audio and video electronic products, such as cable lines; and satellite TV equipment and antenna products. It is also involved in the installation and integration of signal systems and traffic communication networks; and provision of direct-to-home services for satellite TV broadcasting. In addition, the company trades in optical fiber products; and offers services for integration system of public programs. It has operations in Asia, Europe, North America, the Middle East, Africa, South America, and internationally. Sandmartin International Holdings Limited was founded in 1987 and is headquartered in Sheung Wan, Hong Kong.

Bauhaus International (Holdings) Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the design and retail of apparel, bags, and fashion accessories for men and women. As of March 31, 2019, the company operated a network of 73 stores under the BAUHAUS, SALAD, TOUGH, 80/20, and SUPERDRY brand names. It also sells its products through online channels. In addition, the company engages in the property holding activities; trading of garments and accessories; and provision of management services. It operates in Hong Kong, Macau, Taiwan, Mainland China, and internationally. The company was founded in 1991 and is headquartered in Kowloon Bay, Hong Kong. Bauhaus International (Holdings) Limited is a subsidiary of Huge Treasure Investments Limited.

Forgame Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, develops, publishes, and operates Webgames and mobile games in the People's Republic of China. The company operates through two segments, Game Business and Fintech Business. It also operates 91wan, a game publishing platform. In addition, it provides information technology, finance information technology, and finance and investment consulting, as well as management consulting services; software development services; and Internet micro-credit services. The company was founded in 2009 and is headquartered in Guangzhou, the People's Republic of China.

China Sinostar Group Company Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the design and sale of electronic products. Its electronic products include consumer electronic audio and video equipment, karaoke equipment, and accessories. The company is also involved in the operation and management of hydroelectric power stations; development and sale of properties; and properties investment and securities trading activities. In addition, it trades in consumer karaoke audio equipment, and electronic products and appliances. China Sinostar Group Company Limited operates in the United States, Canada, Europe, the People's Republic of China, and internationally. The company was formerly known as Shihua Development Company Limited and changed its name to China Sinostar Group Company Limited in October 2016. The company was founded in 1969 and is based in Hung Hom, Hong Kong. China Sinostar Group Company Limited is a subsidiary of Achieve Prosper Capital Limited.

United Company RUSAL Plc produces and sells aluminum and related products. It operates through Aluminium, Alumina, Energy, and Mining and Metals segments. The company is involved in the mining and refining of bauxite and nepheline ore into alumina; the smelting of primary aluminium from alumina; and the fabrication of aluminium and aluminium alloys into semi-fabricated and finished products. Its products include primary aluminum, aluminum alloys, high purity aluminum, wire rods, aluminum foil and packaging products, aluminum coarse and fine powders, bauxite and alumina, silicon, gallium, corundum, anticorrosion aluminum protectors, cast aluminum wheels, and silica fume. The company is also involved in the mining and sale of coal; generation and transmission of electricity produced from various sources; trading business; and the provision of repair and maintenance, and finance services. In addition, it manufactures semi-finished products from primary aluminium for the transportation, packaging, building and construction, consumer goods, and technology industries. The company sells its products primarily in Europe, Russia, other countries of the Commonwealth of Independent States, Asia, and North America. United Company RUSAL Plc was founded in 2000 and is based in Saint Helier, the Channel Islands.

Success Universe Group Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the travel-related and property investment businesses in the Hong Kong and North America. The company offers travel related services; and sells airline tickets and tour packages. The company also operates Ponte 16, an integrated casino-entertainment resort comprising a five-star luxury hotel-Sofitel Macau At Ponte 16, a casino, and food and beverage facilities; and provides administration services. In addition, it leases office premises and sells properties. The company was formerly known as Macau Success Limited and changed its name to Success Universe Group Limited in June 2009. Success Universe Group Limited was founded in 2003 and is headquartered in Wanchai, Hong Kong. Success Universe Group Limited is a subsidiary of Silver Rich Macau Development Limited.

Lai Sun Development Company Limited, together with its subsidiaries, invests in, develops, leases, and sells real estate properties in Hong Kong, the United Kingdom, Vietnam, and internationally. It operates through Property Development and Sales, Property Investment, Restaurant Operation, Hotel Operation, and Others segments. The company also invests in, develops, operates, and manages hotels and restaurants; and provides management and consultancy services to hotels and restaurants. In addition, it offers property management, real estate agency, leasing agency, and building services; and luxury yachts brokerage, charter, marketing, management, and crew placement services; and finance and treasury services, as well as engages in golf apparel retailing. The company is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong. Lai Sun Development Company Limited is a subsidiary of Lai Sun Garment (International) Limited.

Emperor Culture Group Limited, an investment holding company, engages in entertainment, media, and cultural development businesses in the People's Republic of China. It develops and operates cinemas; invests in films; invests in various cultural events, including music concerts, live shows, theatrical performances, etc.; and invests in securities. The company was formerly known as See Corporation Limited and changed its name to Emperor Culture Group Limited in June 2017. Emperor Culture Group Limited was incorporated in 1992 and is headquartered in Wanchai, Hong Kong. Emperor Culture Group Limited is a subsidiary of Albert Yeung Entertainment Holdings Limited.

GOME Retail Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the retail of home appliances and consumer electronic products in the People's Republic of China. The company is also involved in the provision of logistics and procurement, storage and delivery, IT development, and business management services; retailing of mobile phones and accessories; and online retail of electrical appliances and consumer electronic products, as well as in property holding activities. In addition, it engages in the trading of wine products. As of December 31, 2018, it operated 2,122 stores in 606 cities.
