Easy Repay Finance & Investment Limited engages in the retail and wholesale of grocery products in Hong Kong. The company sells grocery products, such as frozen food through retail and online channels. It is also involved in money lending; and financial instruments and quoted shares investment businesses. In addition, the company offers beauty and clinical, online advertising, and video filming services; and trades in cash coupons. The company was formerly known as Unlimited Creativity Holdings Limited and changed its name to Easy Repay Finance & Investment Limited in April 2015. Easy Repay Finance & Investment Limited is headquartered in Cheung Sha Wan, Hong Kong.

North Asia Strategic Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the hi-tech distribution and services, and leasing businesses in the People's Republic of China and rest of Asia. The company's Hi-Tech Distribution and Services segment trades in surface mount technology (SMT) assembly equipment, machinery, and spare parts; and provides installation, training, repair, and maintenance services for SMT assembly equipment. Its Leasing segment provides finance to its customers through a range of assets under finance and operating lease arrangements. The company also offers management services. North Asia Strategic Holdings Limited is based in Central, Hong Kong.

Hang Tai Yue Group Holdings Limited, through its subsidiaries, engages in the mobile Internet cultural and IT services, hospitality and related, money lending, and assets investments businesses in Hong Kong, the People's Republic of China, and Australia. The company's Mobile Internet Cultural Business and Provision of IT Services segment provides enterprise software and mobile Internet applications, platform development outsourcing services, mainframe downsizing, application localization, and systems integration services, as well as designs, develops, markets, distributes, and operates mobile-online games. Its Provision of Hospitality and Related Services in Australia segment operates resorts under the Prestige Retreats Group of Resorts brand. The company's Money Lending Business segment provides unsecured loans to individual customers. Its Assets Investments Business segment invests in securities and properties. The company was formerly known as Interactive Entertainment China Cultural Technology Investments Limited and changed its name to Hang Tai Yue Group Holdings Limited in November 2018. Hang Tai Yue Group Holdings Limited was incorporated in 2000 and is headquartered in Sheung Wan, Hong Kong.
longName: Hang Tai Yue Group Holdings Limited

longBusinessSummary: Sage International Group Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the media and entertainment business in Hong Kong, Macao, and Mainland China. It operates in two segments, Media and Entertainment, and Funeral Services. The company invests in concert and film production projects, as well as produces online dramas and films. It also offers drama and musical performance production, artist management, and music intellectual property rights management services, as well as administrative services; and holds a club membership. In addition, the company provides cremation, funeral arrangement, and funeral services; and manages cemeteries. The company was formerly known as Info Communication Holdings Limited and changed its name to Sage International Group Limited in September 2010. Sage International Group Limited was incorporated in 2001 and is headquartered in Kwun Tong, Hong Kong.

China Youzan Limited, an investment holding company, provides third party payment and related consultancy services in the People's Republic of China. It operates through four segments: General Trading, Third Party Payment Services, Onecomm, and Merchant Service. The company provides Internet payment, cross-border Renminbi payment, and prepaid card services; and third party payment management services, as well as sells integrated smart point of sales devices. In addition, it offers merchant services, such as e-commerce Software as a Service (SaaS) platform, store SaaS, distribution, advertising, value-added, and PaaS cloud services. Further, it trades watches and other goods; and information system maintenance and development services. The company was formerly known as China Innovationpay Group Limited and changed its name to China Youzan Limited in May 2018. China Youzan Limited was incorporated in 1999 and is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong.

Hong Kong Life Sciences and Technologies Group Limited, an investment holding company, engages in anti-aging and stem cell technology, trading, money lending, and securities investment businesses in the People's Republic of China. The company provides anti-aging, health check and beauty, and stem cell anti-aging application related services, as well as stem cell storage and processing services; and distributes biomedical and life science products. It also leases anti-aging service platform; trades in electronic components and healthcare products; provides secured and unsecured loans to individuals and corporate customers; and trades and invests in securities. The company was formerly known as ZMAY Holdings Limited and changed its name to Hong Kong Life Sciences and Technologies Group Limited in October 2012. Hong Kong Life Sciences and Technologies Group Limited was incorporated in 2000 and is based in Central, Hong Kong.
longName: Hong Kong Life Sciences and Technologies Group Limited

longBusinessSummary: China 33 Media Group Limited, an investment holding company, operates as a channel media provider for high-speed railway network in the People's Republic of China and internationally. It operates through Printed Media Advertising, Outdoor Advertising, Film and Entertainment Investment, and Prepaid Card segments. The company operates and distributes publications on the high-speed trains and selected regular trains. Its publications include Fellow Traveller, a monthly publication focusing on topical content and infotainment; Shanghai Railway, a monthly publication distributed on high-speed railway passenger trains for the elite groups of business travel; Ever Green, a magazine for the first class cabins of Hainan Airlines; and City Life, a periodical distributed on regular trains and/or high-speed trains. The company also promotes and sells advertising space on the air traffic control towers at civil airports, as well as installs and operates the billboards and LEDs advertisements at various train stations. In addition, it holds production rights for Geographic China, a program of China Central Television's Science & Education Channel; and provides management and consulting services. Further, the company engages in the box office of movies and concerts; and distribution of film rights and television dramas, as well as provision of prepaid card services. China 33 Media Group Limited was incorporated in 2010 and is headquartered in Beijing, the People's Republic of China.

Chinese Strategic Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in tea products trading, properties investment, securities trading, loan financing, and securities and asset management advice businesses in the People's Republic of China and the Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands. It is also involved in the rental of office premises; and project development and office administration activities. The company was formerly known as China Railway Logistics Limited and changed its name to Chinese Strategic Holdings Limited in June 2013. Chinese Strategic Holdings Limited was incorporated in 2000 and is headquartered in Wan Chai, Hong Kong.

China Assurance Finance Group Limited, an investment holding company, provides financial and related consultancy services to small and medium-sized enterprises in the People's Republic of China. The company operates through three segments: Financial Guarantee and Consultancy Services, Software Development Services, and Online Trading Platform Services. It also develops and sells computer application software systems, as well as provides maintenance services. In addition, the company provides electronic market services for the transaction of commodity, including non-ferrous and ferrous metal, agricultural products, energy products, chemical materials, and machineries and equipment. Further, it engages in trading and retail businesses. The company was incorporated in 2011 and is headquartered in Zhangjiakou, the People's Republic of China.

OOH Holdings Limited provides out-of-home advertising space and services in Hong Kong and internationally. It offers advertising display services on minibuses, taxis, and inside hospitals, clinics, and health and beauty retail stores, as well as digital and online media platforms. The company also provides esports event management services; and design and production, advertisement logistics, installation, and dismantling services on various advertising platforms. It serves customers in various markets, such as pharmaceutical, healthcare, beauty, food and beverage, home design and furniture industries, etc. The company was founded in 2004 and is based in Kwun Tong, Hong Kong.

ITE (Holdings) Limited, an investment holding company, provides smartcard systems, radio frequency identification (RFID) products, and information technology (IT) and related services to the public and private sectors in Hong Kong and Macao. The company offers various evaluation kits based on RFID technologies; smartcard and RFID readers for professional PDA products; and Octopus access control systems for residential and commercial use, as well as distributes Minec handheld data collection terminals. It also designs and provides customized products, including contact and contactless readers, smart meters, processing units and controllers, terminals and kiosks, antennas, etc. In addition, it offers IT services, such as software application design, development, and implementation services; software application enhancement and system maintenance services; system integration services; and IT evaluation and operation services comprising feasibility studies, training, and system performance tuning. Further, the company provides contract staff and executive search consulting services; and project management, hardware development, equipment and component supply, and after-sales and maintenance services. ITE (Holdings) Limited was founded in 1997 and is headquartered in Kowloon, Hong Kong.

Million Stars Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides programmatic advertising services. It provides Internet advertising agency services, which includes streaming advertising, search engine advertising, and applied marketing and navigation advertising; promotion of online game; and mobile payment technical support services. The company was formerly known as Odella Leather Holdings Limited and changed its name to Million Stars Holdings Limited in May 2017. Million Stars Holdings Limited was founded in 1988 and is headquartered in Tsim Sha Tsui, Hong Kong.

Beijing Beida Jade Bird Universal Sci-Tech Company Limited, together with its subsidiaries, manufactures, markets, and sells embedded system products and related products in the People's Republic of China, the United States, Canada, and internationally. It operates through Manufacture and Sale of Electronic Fire Equipment, Tourism Development, and All Other segments. The company is involved in the research, development, manufacture, marketing, and sale of electronic fire alarm systems, fire alarm system software, and related products, as well as security and fire equipment products. It also engages in the travel and leisure business; production and sale of wine and related products; and provision of investment management and advisory services. The company is headquartered in Beijing, the People's Republic of China.
longName: Beijing Beida Jade Bird Universal Sci-Tech Company Limited

longBusinessSummary: CL Group (Holdings) Limited, an investment holding company, provides various financial services in Hong Kong and the People's Republic of China. It offers securities, futures, and options brokering and trading services; loan financing services; placing and underwriting services; margin financing and money lending services; securities advisory services; and wealth management services. The company is headquartered in Wanchai, Hong Kong. CL Group (Holdings) Limited is a subsidiary of Zillion Profit Limited.
address1: Bank of East Asia Harbour View Centre

longBusinessSummary: GET Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the research, development, and distribution of personal computer performance software, anti-virus software, mobile phone applications, and toolbar advertisements. It offers corporate management solutions, information technology (IT) contract services, network infrastructure solutions, network professional services, and IT project implementation services, as well as sells hardware and software. The company also engages in online shopping and property investment business; and provision of children education services and training programs. GET Holdings Limited operates in Hong Kong, the United States, Russia, Japan, Germany, the United Kingdom, Canada, Australia, and internationally. The company was formerly known as M Dream Inworld Limited and changed its name to GET Holdings Limited in November 2014. GET Holdings Limited was incorporated in 2001 and is headquartered in Wanchai, Hong Kong.

EJE (Hong Kong) Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, manufactures and sells custom-made furniture in the People's Republic of China and internationally. The company offers home furniture-mattresses, and soft bed and healthy concept products. It is also involved in the property and securities investment activities, as well as money lending business. The company was formerly known as Jia Meng Holdings Limited and changed its name to EJE (Hong Kong) Holdings Limited in January 2018. EJE (Hong Kong) Holdings Limited was incorporated in 2012 and is based in Central, Hong Kong.

hmvod Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the provision of professional services, proprietary trading activities, money lending business, and over the top services in the People's Republic of China. Its OTT services segment produces and distributes films, television programs, and music. The company's Professional Services segment offers information technology (IT) engineering and technical support services, including financial valuation and IT services. Its Proprietary Trading segment is involved in trading listed securities. The company's Money Lending segment provides financing services. The company is also involved in the research, development, and provision of integrated management information systems; and provision of services and solutions on cyber security. In addition, it provides content services. The company was formerly known as Trillion Grand Corporate Company Limited and changed its name to hmvod Limited in October 2018. The company is based in Cheung Sha Wan, Hong Kong.

Kingsley Edugroup Limited, an investment holding company, operates as a private education service provider in Malaysia. The company operates through two segments, International School and Tertiary Education. It offers courses from nursery to A-levels; and tertiary education programs. The company operates various schools and colleges. In addition, it offers skills training programs; and is involved in the organization, promotion, and/or management of event meeting incentive, convention, and exhibition, as well as provision of business advisory and consultancy services in public relations and communications. The company was founded in 2010 and is headquartered in Subang Jaya, Malaysia. Kingsley Edugroup Limited is a subsidiary of Star Shine Finance Limited.

Shenghua Lande Scitech Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the trading of hardware and computer software in the People's Republic of China. The company also provides telecommunication solutions; telecommunication value-added services; smart city solutions; and e-commerce supply chain services. Its businesses include SMS business cards, precise marketing, and 114 Bai Shi Tong Alliance. The company was formerly known as Zheda Lande Scitech Limited and changed its name to Shenghua Lande Scitech Limited in June 2017. Shenghua Lande Scitech Limited was founded in 1996 and is based in Huzhou, the People's Republic of China.

Vision International Holdings Limited provides apparel supply chain management services primarily in Europe and Asia. It offers market trend analysis, product design and development, supplier sourcing, production management, logistics, and quality control services. The company was founded in 2010 and is headquartered in Kowloon, Hong Kong.

Grand Peace Group Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides funeral services in the People's Republic of China. It also sells funeral related products; and offers loan financing services. The company was formerly known as FAVA International Holdings Limited and changed its name to Grand Peace Group Holdings Limited in September 2014. Grand Peace Group Holdings Limited is headquartered in Wanchai, Hong Kong.

Kirin Group Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides insurance brokerage and money lending services in Hong Kong. The company operates through Insurance Brokerage and Related Service; Asset Management and Securities Brokerage Service; Money Lending Service; and Sales of Livestocks segments. It also offers advisory services, asset management services, and securities brokerage services, as well as consultancy services. The company was formerly known as Creative Energy Solutions Holdings Limited and changed its name to Kirin Group Holdings Limited in July 2016. Kirin Group Holdings Limited is headquartered in Wan Chai, Hong Kong.

China Technology Solar Power Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, primarily provides solar power related products in the People's Republic of China. It is involved in the research and development, sale, and provision of other relevant technology consultation services for photovoltaic mounting brackets, solar trackers, and the guardrail of the solar power stations and solar power related products. The company also provides power system integration services, as well as system management services to the power stations. In addition, it sells self-service ATM and printing systems; and provides hardware and software technical support services. Further, the company offers designs and develops network communication and system software products, as well as related technical and consultation services; sells self-produced products; and provides technical support services for computer communication systems. The company was formerly known as Soluteck Holdings Limited and changed its name to China Technology Solar Power Holdings Limited in August 2011. China Technology Solar Power Holdings Limited is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong.
longName: China Technology Solar Power Holdings Limited

longBusinessSummary: Hi-Level Technology Holdings Limited, an independent design house (IDH), engages in the sale of electronic components in the People's Republic of China, Hong Kong, Taiwan, and internationally. It offers integrated circuit and panels for consumer electronic products, such as mobile Internet devices, electronic learning aids, multi-media players, smartphone panel modules, set-top boxes, video image devices, tablets, CVRs, Wi-Fi modules and connectors, digital cameras, sport cameras, drone cameras, e-books, wearable devices, and other products. The company offers its IDH services to original design manufacturers and original brand manufacturers. Hi-Level Technology Holdings Limited was founded in 2000 and is based in Hung Hom, Hong Kong.

Shanghai Qingpu Fire-Fighting Equipment Co., Ltd., together with its subsidiaries, manufactures and sells firefighting equipment and pressure vessel products in the People's Republic of China, the United States, the European Union, and internationally. The company operates through seven segments: Fire-Fighting Equipment, Inspection Services, Grooved Couplings, Trading, Aquarium Products, Marine Fire-Fighting, and Property Investment. It also provides fire technology inspection services; installs and inspects marine fire-fighting equipment; manufactures and trades in iron casted grooved couplings; trades in sanitary-ware and other products; and invests in and rents office buildings and industrial properties, as well as sells aquarium products. The company was formerly known as Shanghai Qingpu Fire-Fighting Equipment Factory and changed its name to Shanghai Qingpu Fire-Fighting Equipment Co., Ltd. in December 2000. The company is based in North Point, Hong Kong. Shanghai Qingpu Fire-Fighting Equipment Co., Ltd. is a subsidiary of Liancheng Fire-Fighting Group Company Limited.
longName: Shanghai Qingpu Fire-Fighting Equipment Co., Ltd.

longBusinessSummary: China Primary Energy Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, primarily engages in the transmission and distribution of natural gas in the People's Republic of China and Honk Kong. The company operates through Transmission and Distribution of Natural Gas, Trading of Electronic Components, and Property Investment segments. It also engages in the development and use of energy technology, as well as provides promotion and technical consulting services. In addition, the company trades in composite materials. The company was formerly known as China Primary Resources Holdings Limited. China Primary Energy Holdings Limited was incorporated in 2001 and is headquartered in Tsim Sha Tsui, Hong Kong.

Bortex Global Limited, an investment holding company, develops, manufactures, and exports light-emitting diode (LED) lighting products to customers in Canada, Taiwan, the United States, Hong Kong, the People's Republic of China, Brazil, France, Japan, the Philippines, Thailand, South Africa, and Italy. The company offers LED decorative and string lights products, including straight line, icicle, beard garland, crab, wreath, flower, meteor shower, sphere, net, and smart string lights, as well as toy and tree lights; LED commercial lighting products, such as tube lights, ceiling lamps, and light bulbs; and LED solar system series products. It serves retailers, wholesalers, real estate developers, and other fields, as well as agricultural technology production companies. Bortex Global Limited was founded in 2014 and is headquartered in Kwun Tong, Hong Kong.

Thiz Technology Group Limited, an investment holding company, develops and promotes Linux operating systems and office software in the People's Republic of China. The company operates in three segments: Trading Business, Software Development, and Property Leasing. The Trading Business segment trades in computer accessories and household goods. The Software Development segment develops fintech related customized software/applications; and provides related services, as well as technical support and other auxiliary services relating to Linux-based systems and others. The Property Leasing segment leases office properties. The company also invests in properties. Thiz Technology Group Limited was founded in 1998 and is headquartered in To Kwa Wan, Hong Kong.

China Demeter Financial Investments Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the development, manufacturing, and distribution of feedstock products in the People's Republic of China. The company operates through eight segments: Agricultural, Money Lending, Financial Services, Securities Investment, Food and Beverage, Alcoholic Distribution, and Kindergarten. It offers loan financing services to individuals and companies; advises and deals in securities and asset management; and invests in listed and unlisted securities. In addition, the company distributes craft beer in Hong Kong and the Peoples Republic of China; and operates 7 restaurants in Hong Kong and Singapore. Additionally, it offers pre-school education services, as well as operates child care center. The company was formerly known as China Demeter Investments Limited and changed its name to China Demeter Financial Investments Limited in December 2016. China Demeter Financial Investments Limited was incorporated in 2000 and is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong.

Guru Online (Holdings) Limited, an investment holding company, provides integrated digital marketing services in Hong Kong and the People's Republic of China. The company operates through Digital Advertisement Placement Services, Social Media Management Services, and Creative and Technology Services segments. It offers advertisement placement services through digital media; and set-up, maintenance, and monitor services on corporate profile pages through the social media platforms, as well as operates Internet marketing platform for the travel industry. The company is also involved in the design and copywriting of digital advertisements; production of corporate profile pages, and Website and apps, as well as provision of related consultancy services; and provision of marketing services. Guru Online (Holdings) Limited was founded in 2007 and is headquartered in Kwun Tong, Hong Kong.

Sinofortune Financial Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides a range of financial services in the People's Republic of China and Hong Kong. The company offers securities and futures brokerage, and securities margin financing services; and precious metals brokerage and spot trading services. It also provides securities and futures contract trading and wealth management services; and involved in the trading and principal investment activities. In addition, the company offers a trading platform; corporate finance solutions; asset management; stock information and research services through the Internet network, as well as researches, explores, develops, and sells student safety products and electronic student cards. Further, it engages in property holding; development and design of television programs and artworks; development and sale of software for information network equipment, terminal products, and calculators; and the trading of electronic student cards and school safety products. Additionally, Sinofortune Financial Holdings Limited sells motor vehicles and provides agency services The company was formerly known as First China Financial Network Holdings Limited and changed its name to Sinofortune Financial Holdings Limited in June 2017. Sinofortune Financial Holdings Limited was incorporated in 2001 and is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong.

Royal Century Resources Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides design and fitting-out services in Hong Kong. The company also engages in the design and procurement of furnishings and decorative materials; and property investment and money lending businesses. In addition, it is involved in sourcing, merchandising, and trading of wines, spirits, furniture, and marbles; advising on securities and securities dealing and brokerage activities; provision of asset management services; and leasing of construction equipment. Further, the company offers interior design and decoration services. The company was formerly known as Kate China Holdings Limited and changed its name to Royal Century Resources Holdings Limited in February 2017. Royal Century Resources Holdings Limited was founded in 2004 and is headquartered in Wan Chai, Hong Kong.

G.A. Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the sale of motor vehicles and provision of car-related technical services in Singapore, Hong Kong, and the People's Republic of China. It operates through two segments, Motor Vehicles Sales and Services Business, and Car Rental Business. The company distributes a range of luxury and ultra-luxury motor vehicles of various brands, such as BMW, Mini, Ferrari, and Maserati. It is also involved in the wholesale and retail of original auto parts and accessories of BMW, Mini Cooper, Ferrari, and Maserati, as well as operates as an authorized distributor of AC Schnitzer. In addition, the company operates authorized service centers that offers repair and maintenance services for high-end automobiles; and operates as a licensee of the Hertz car rental services. Further, the company engages in the automobile dealership and motor vehicles exhibition business. G.A. Holdings Limited was founded in 1993 and is headquartered in Singapore.

China Geothermal Industry Development Group Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the field of promoting the geothermal ground source energy as alternative energy for heating in the People's Republic of China. The company operates through Shallow Geothermal Energy, Air Conditioning Heat Pump, Properties Investment and Development, and Securities Investment and Trading segments. The Shallow Geothermal Energy segment engages in the provision, installation, and maintenance of shallow geothermal energy utilization systems. The Air Conditioning Heat Pump segment trades in air conditioning heat pump products. The Properties Investment and Development segment invests in properties. The Securities Investment and Trading segment invests its funds for trading of securities and other types of investments. The company also provides property management and technical support services; and installs energy systems. The company was formerly known as China Ground Source Energy Industry Group Limited and changed its name to China Geothermal Industry Development Group Limited in May 2018. China Geothermal Industry Development Group Limited was incorporated in 1999 and is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong.
longName: China Geothermal Industry Development Group Limited

longBusinessSummary: Dadi International Group Limited, an investment holding company, provides advertising and media related, and financial leasing and other financial services in the People's Republic of China. The company engages in the designing, production, and placement of advertisements; and provision of information consulting and marketing planning services, as well as advertisement agency services. It is also involved in securities investment activities. The company was formerly known as Zhi Cheng Holdings Limited and changed its name to Dadi International Group Limited in May 2019. Dadi International Group Limited was incorporated in 2001 and is headquartered in Wan Chai, Hong Kong.

abc Multiactive Limited, through its subsidiaries, designs and sells computer software primarily in the Asia Pacific region. The company offers OCTO STP, a trading software package that is used for front and back-office trading in brokerages and securities divisions of banks. The company's front office dealer trading system includes OCTO SPIDER, unit trust, EIPO, bonds/notes, hold fund module, and gold futures modules; back office settlement system comprises FRR, EIPO, unit trust, bonds/notes, document image management, ELI/ELN, OASYS, email/fax gateway plugin, and fax confirmation modules for equity, futures, and equity options. It also provides Internet trading solutions, including Web pages module for trading through Internet; and Fortune Maker, an application for AE or client to use through Internet, as well as mobile trading solutions. In addition, the company offers global trading support services for multi-products, channels, and market trade; real-time risk management; and comprehensive order types, as well as wealth management solutions. Further, it provides FINCAD analytics suite, a derivatives and fixed income analytics solutions for valuations; F3 solution for valuing virtually any financial structure or payoff; automated reporting solutions for treasuries; and systems integration services. Additionally, the company offers professional and maintenance services for its products; and risk management services. The company was incorporated in 1978 and is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong. abc Multiactive Limited is a subsidiary of Maximizer International Limited.

China Oil Gangran Energy Group Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the power and data cords, digital application, and refined oil and chemicals trading businesses. It operates in three segments: Trading of Refined Oil and Chemicals; Digital Application Business; and Power and Data Cords and General Trading Business. The company manufactures and sells power cords and inlet sockets for household electric appliances; power and data cords for mobile handsets and medical control devices; and raw cables. It also trades in mobile smart phones and glasses; provides programming services, Web services, and mobile marketing solutions; and develops mobile phone games. In addition, the company engages in the liquefied natural gas, compressed natural gas, and other related clean energy businesses; refined oil retail business; trading of methyl tert-butyl ether; and development and trading of refined oil and chemicals. It has operations in Hong Kong, the People's Republic of China, Taiwan, the United States, and internationally. The company was formerly known as Fairson Holdings Limited and changed its name to China Oil Gangran Energy Group Holdings Limited in April 2014. China Oil Gangran Energy Group Holdings Limited was incorporated in 2010 and is based in Central, Hong Kong.
longName: China Oil Gangran Energy Group Holdings Limited

longBusinessSummary: Jete Power Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, manufactures and sells cast metal products in Germany, Hong Kong, the People's Republic of China, the United States, and internationally. It operates through two segments, Metal Casting and Entertainment. The company provides pump, filter, valve, and food machinery components made from stainless steel, carbon steel, bronze, and/or grey iron. It serves suppliers of flow control devices, electromechanical equipment, and industrial machinery and equipment. The company also organizes concerts and events. Jete Power Holdings Limited was incorporated in 2014 and is headquartered in Kwai Chung, Hong Kong.

ZMFY Automobile Glass Services Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the sale of automobile glass with installation/repair services for private and public motor vehicles in the People's Republic of China. It operates through four segments: Automobile Glass, Photovoltaic System, Business Consultancy Services, and Finance Leasing Services. The company also trades in automobile glass to industry peers and the traders of automobile glass; and provides photovoltaic system installation, business consultancy, and finance leasing services. It primarily serves insurance companies, and corporate and individual customers. The company operates 21 service centers. ZMFY Automobile Glass Services Limited was founded in 1999 and is headquartered in Beijing, the People's Republic of China.

IMS Group Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, designs and sells light-emitting diode (LED) lighting products for retail stores of luxury brands in Hong Kong and internationally. The company offers LED lighting fixtures; integrated LED lighting solution services, such as LED lighting system design; LED lighting system consultation and maintenance services; after-delivery maintenance and enhancement services; and on-site project management services. It also sells visual-audio systems, including audio/video conference, projection, public address, sound masking, and central controlling systems. IMS Group Holdings Limited was founded in 1998 and is based in North Point, Hong Kong.

Honbridge Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the research and development, production, and sale of lithium batteries and battery systems in the People's Republic of China, Belgium, and Sweden. It operates through Mineral Resources Exploration and Trading; and Lithium Battery Production segments. The company's principal products include ternary lithium-ion powered batteries, lithium-iron phosphate powered batteries, powered battery modules, battery management systems, and storage batteries primarily for new energy commercial vehicles, passenger vehicles, and purely electric and hybrid vehicles, as well as for energy storage market. It also researches and explores mineral resources, and trades in copper and steel. In addition, the company researches and explores for iron ores in Brazil. The company is headquartered in Wanchai, Hong Kong. Honbridge Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Hong Bridge Capital Limited.

Zhejiang Chang'an Renheng Technology Co., Ltd., together with its subsidiaries, develops, produces, and sells bentonite fine chemicals in the People's Republic of China. The company offers papermaking chemicals; bentonite products for metallurgy pellets; quality calcium-bentonite products; organic bentonite products; and other chemicals, such as flocculating agents that are primarily used in the coating preparation industry. It is also involved in the mining and processing of clay; and wholesale and retail of chemicals and equipment. The company was formerly known as Changxing Renheng Fine Bentonite Co., Ltd. and changed its name to Zhejiang Chang'an Renheng Technology Co., Ltd. in December 2008. Zhejiang Chang'an Renheng Technology Co., Ltd. was founded in 2000 and is headquartered in Changxing, the People's Republic of China.
longName: Zhejiang Chang'an Renheng Technology Co., Ltd.

longBusinessSummary: BOSA Technology Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides mechanical splicing services to the reinforced concrete construction industry in Hong Kong. It is involved in processing reinforcing bars, including cutting, crimping, chamfering, and threading of reinforcing bars at its premises or at the premises of customers; and connecting reinforcing bars by couplers. The company was founded in 2012 and is headquartered in Kwun Tong, Hong Kong.

Tak Lee Machinery Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the sale and leasing of new and used earthmoving equipment in Hong Kong. The company operates through Sales of Heavy Equipment and Spare Parts, Lease of Heavy Equipment, and Maintenance and Ancillary Services segments. It sells and leases heavy equipment, such as excavators, bulldozers, lifting cranes, hydraulic breakers, and others; and sells spare parts. In addition, it provides maintenance and ancillary services; and motor vehicles services. The company was incorporated in 2015 and is headquartered in Yuen Long, Hong Kong. Tak Lee Machinery Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Generous Way Limited.

Good Fellow Healthcare Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides general hospital services in Mainland China and internationally. Its general hospital services include medical and surgical ward, cosmetic surgery, dermatology, and medical checkup and examination. As of March 31, 2019, the company operated three general hospitals in Jiaxing, Zhuhai, and Beijing. It also provides medical investment and hospital management services. The company was formerly known as Hua Xia Healthcare Holdings Limited and changed its name to Good Fellow Healthcare Holdings Limited in February 2019. Good Fellow Healthcare Holdings Limited was incorporated in 2001 and is headquartered in Hong Kong, Hong Kong.

Grace Wine Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the production and distribution of wine products under the Grace Vineyard brand name in the People's Republic of China. It offers red, white, and sparkling types of wine. Grace Wine Holdings Limited was founded in 1997 and is based in Quarry Bay, Hong Kong.

Millennium Pacific Group Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the research and development, manufacture, and sale of consumer electronic products. The company offers fitness bracelets, GPS personal navigation devices, mobile Internet devices, digital video recorders, and TV set-top boxes. It also trades in electronic devices; provides data management services; and develops and sells software applications. In addition, the company provides design, prototyping/sampling, manufacturing, assembling, and packaging services to customers' products. It has operations in the People's Republic of China, Hong Kong, the United Kingdom, the Netherlands, Germany, and internationally. The company was founded in 2004 and is headquartered in Shenzhen, the People's Republic of China.

Aurum Pacific (China) Group Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the development and marketing of patented server based technology, and provision of communications software platform and software related services. The company operates in Software Platform, Money Lending, and Mobile Gaming segments. Its information technology solutions facilitate government departments and corporations to communicate with their clients via Websites, telephones, and mobile phones using interactive voice response system and mobile applications. The company also engages in the money lending business. In addition, it is involved in the game publishing business; development of mobile games and applications, and related intellectual property and platform; and provision of related solutions. In addition, it offers custom-made software development services. The company has operations in Hong Kong, Mainland China, and internationally. The company was formerly known as S & D International Development Group Limited and changed its name to Aurum Pacific (China) Group Limited in November 2008. Aurum Pacific (China) Group Limited is headquartered in Wanchai, Hong Kong.

Altus Holdings Limited provides corporate finance and property investment services in Hong Kong. The company operates through Corporate Finance Services and Property Investment. It offers corporate finance services, including sponsorship, financial advisory, and compliance advisory services. The company also leases investment properties for residential and commercial use; and provides administrative services. Altus Holdings Limited was founded in 2000 and is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong. Altus Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Kinley-Hecico Holdings Limited.

Seamless Green China (Holdings) Limited, an investment holding company, manufactures and trades in LED and related products in the People's Republic of China, Hong Kong, and the Philippines. The company operates through LED, Optoelectronic, Liquor, and Sapphire segments. It supplies optoelectronic products and watch crystals for use in the watch products. The company also engages in the trading of wine and optoelectronic products; and property investment activities. Seamless Green China (Holdings) Limited was incorporated in 2001 and is headquartered in Sheung Wan, Hong Kong.

Bao Shen Holdings Limited engages in manufacturing and processing of plastic and steel components for white goods in the People's Republic of China. The company offers stamping components and peripheral components that are used in the assembling of white goods, including home washing machines and home refrigerators. It is also involved in processing of spray-painting components and powder-coating components. It primarily sells its products to component processors and white goods manufacturers. Bao Shen Holdings Limited was founded in 2010 and is headquartered in Chuzhou, the Peoples Republic of China. Bao Shen Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Wang Mao Investments Limited.

M&L Holdings Group Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the trading and leasing of construction machinery and spare parts primarily in Hong Kong, the People's Republic of China, and Singapore. The company operates through two segments, Tunnelling and Foundation. It supplies specialized cutting tools and parts for tunnelling equipment manufacturers; and disc cutters, as well as specialized construction equipment. The company also provides fabricated construction steel works and equipment; and repair and maintenance services. M&L Holdings Group Limited was founded in 1994 and is headquartered in Tsimshatsui, Hong Kong. M&L Holdings Group Limited is a subsidiary of JAT United Company Limited.

Code Agriculture (Holdings) Limited, an investment holding company, provides digital television, broadcasting, and advertising services in the People's Republic of China. It also offers movie production and distribution services; and short-term personal and property mortgage loans, as well as invests and trades in securities. The company was formerly known as China Chief Cable TV Group Limited. Code Agriculture (Holdings) Limited was founded in 2000 and is headquartered in Wan Chai, Hong Kong.

South China Assets Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the property investment and development businesses in the People's Republic of China. It operates through two segments, Property Development and Financial Services. The company undertakes mixed development projects, which comprise commercial/retail, residential, and office/hotel projects, as well as shopping mall, entertainment, dining, and recreational facilities. It is also involved in money lending business; and the provision of investment advisory and asset management services, as well as deals in securities and futures, and insurance and mandatory provident fund service. The company was formerly known as South China Land Limited and changed its name to South China Assets Holdings Limited in January 2016. South China Assets Holdings Limited is based in Central, Hong Kong.

Sinopharm Tech Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in lottery business in the People's Republic of China and Hong Kong. It operates through Provision of Lottery-Related Services, Provision of Internet Plus Services, and Other Services segments. The company offers lottery-related hardware and software systems. It also provides Internet plus solution services to government affair, public security, health care, leasing, and lottery industries; and corporate management, and food and catering services. The company was formerly known as China Vanguard You Champion Holdings Limited and changed its name to Sinopharm Tech Holdings Limited in June 2019. Sinopharm Tech Holdings Limited was founded in 1999 and is headquartered in Tai Po, Hong Kong.

China Regenerative Medicine International Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the research and development of bio-medical and healthcare products, and medical techniques. It operates through Dermatology, Cosmetic products, and others; Cell and Healthcare products and services; Ophthalmology products; Stomatology products and others; and Medical Equipment segments. The company offers ActivSkin, a tissue-engineered skin product; Acornea, an acellular corneal stroma; Gegreen, a protein-detracted bone substitute material for inducing natural bone regeneration; Asiunin, an acellular anal fistula repair stroma; Megreen, an oral cavity repair membrane; and CS-ACI, a cell sheet-autologous chondrocyte implantation. It also manufactures and sells skincare products under the AMYbio and Ascara brands. In addition, the company owns and operates cell storage, preparation, and therapy centers; develops and produces automated closed cell bioreactors; and sells and distributes medical products and equipment. Further, it offers contract research services, including drug screening, drug efficacy, and toxicity assays to institutions and hospitals. The company was formerly known as China Bio-Med Regeneration Technology Limited and changed its name to China Regenerative Medicine International Limited in March 2015. China Regenerative Medicine International Limited was founded in 1995 and is headquartered in Wanchai, Hong Kong.

Glory Mark Hi-Tech (Holdings) Limited, an investment holding company, designs, manufactures, and sells computer connectivity products. It operates through Original Equipment Manufacturer (OEM) Customers, Retail Distributors, and Provision of Comprehensive Architectural Services segments. The company offers computer peripheral products, multi-media consumable electronic products, communication products, automobile electronics accessories, wire harness, medical equipment, and VGA cables. The company also offers electronic products, such as USB hubs and card readers, cable series, lightning products, docking stations, wireless charging, HDMI, display port, dongles, and adapters. Further, the company is involved in master planning, general design, and architectural schematic design works. It sells its connectivity products to OEM customers and retail distributors in the People's Republic of China, Taiwan, Korea, Japan, the United States, and internationally. Glory Mark Hi-Tech (Holdings) Limited was founded in 1990 and is headquartered in Admiralty, Hong Kong.

Goldway Education Group Limited, an investment holding company, provides tutoring services under the Logic Tutorial Centre name to primary and secondary school students in Hong Kong. It operates through two segments, Primary Tutoring Services and Secondary Tutoring Services. The Primary Tutoring Services segment provides tutoring services to primary school students from primary 1 to 6 who seeks to enhance their performance in formal school and in examination settings; and assists these younger students in solidifying the foundational knowledge necessary for them to succeed through the school system. The Secondary Tutoring Services segment offers tutoring services to secondary school students from secondary 1 to 6 who seeks to enhance their school performance for specific subjects; and prepare for public examinations. As of March 31, 2019, it operated 12 centers, as well as franchise centers in Kowloon and the New Territories. Goldway Education Group Limited was founded in 2003 and is headquartered in Tuen Mun, Hong Kong.

Loco Hong Kong Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in trading of metal and commodity forward contracts in Hong Kong. The company primarily trades in silver, gold, and tin metals, as well as processing of silver products. It also engages in the provision of money lending services. The company serves licensed banks and metal traders in Hong Kong, Singapore, Japan, Taiwan, Australia, the United Kingdom, Dubai, and China. The company was founded in 2009 and is based in Admiralty, Hong Kong.

Merdeka Financial Group Limited, an investment holding company, engages in trading, financial services, and information technology businesses in the People Republic of China. Its Trading Business segment trades in goods, components, and accessories; and retails milk powder, dairy products, beauty and cosmetic products, and pharmaceutical OTC products. The company's Financial Services Business segment provides financial leasing, money lending, asset management, and securities brokerage services; and operates as a book-runner, as well as a lead manager in respect of issuance of debts listed worldwide. Its Information Technology Business segment engages in the distribution of information technology products, and provision of relevant technical support services; developing mobile and cloud based application software; and operating related e-commence platform, as well as franchising a mobile game license. The company's Other Business segment engages in servicing business, such as training course provision. The company was formerly known as Merdeka Financial Services Group Limited and changed its name to Merdeka Financial Group Limited in October 2019. Merdeka Financial Group Limited is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong. Merdeka Financial Group Limited is a subsidiary of Ivana Investments Limited.

China Eco-Farming Limited, an investment holding company, provides one-stop value chain services in Hong Kong, the People's Republic of China, and Taiwan. The company is involved in the provision of value chain services, including trading, packaging, and logistics solutions; and trade of consumables and agricultural products, as well as grocery food products. It also engages in the rental of investment properties; and provision of financial and investment advisory, corporate finance, securities holding, and money lending services, as well as trades in recycle bags. China Eco-Farming Limited has a strategic cooperation agreement with Jinan Rongchao Financial Services Limited and Gulfstream Capital Limited. The company was formerly known as Linefan Technology Holdings Limited and changed its name to China Eco-Farming Limited in October 2009. China Eco-Farming Limited was incorporated in 2000 and is headquartered in Wanchai, Hong Kong.

Neo Telemedia Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the sale of telecommunication products and services in the People's Republic of China. The company operates through Sale of Telecommunication Products and Services; and Internet Finance Platform segments. It also operates commercial WIFI and Internet finance platforms; provides value-added telecommunication and Internet data center services; and designs, manufactures, and sells logistics equipment. In addition, the company trades in mobile phones and tablets; and offers insurance brokerage services. The company was formerly known as Big Media Group Limited and changed its name to Neo Telemedia Limited in November 2009. Neo Telemedia Limited is headquartered in Wan Chai, Hong Kong.

Amasse Capital Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides corporate finance advisory services in Hong Kong. It offers financial advisory services to listed companies and investors seeking to control or invest in public listed companies, as well as to independent board committees and/or independent shareholders of public listed companies. The company was incorporated in 2017 and is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong. Amasse Capital Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Access Cheer Limited.

Eco-Tek Holdings Limited engages in the research, development, marketing, sale, and servicing of industrial environmental protection related products and services in the People's Republic of China and internationally. The company operates through three segments: General Environmental Protection Related Products and Services; Industrial Environmental Products; and Water Supply Plant. It sells particulate removal devices and provides related ancillary services; sells hydraulic components and other related accessories; and supplies processed water. The company was founded in 1999 and is headquartered in Quarry Bay, Hong Kong.

China Trends Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the trading of electronic technology and related products primarily in Hong Kong and Mainland China. It trades in electronic equipment, components, and LCD/LED products. The company also develops low-carbon digital products solutions and applications; and provides media and e-commerce platforms, and media advertising services. China Trends Holdings Limited is headquartered in Sheung Wan, Hong Kong.

Lajin Entertainment Network Group Limited, an investment holding company, provides artists management services in the People's Republic of China and internationally. The company operates in two segments, Artists Management; and Movies, TV Programmes and Internet Contents services. It is also involved in the investment, production, and distribution of movies and TV programs; investment in Internet contents; and digital technology business. The company was formerly known as China Star Cultural Media Group Limited and changed its name to Lajin Entertainment Network Group Limited in August 2015. Lajin Entertainment Network Group Limited was incorporated in 2001 and is headquartered in Admiralty, Hong Kong.

Union Asia Enterprise Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the trading of metals and securities in the People's Republic of China and internationally. The company operates through two segments, Metals and Securities. It is involved in the trading of stainless steel; and investment and trading of securities. The company was formerly known as Pan Asia Mining Limited and changed its name to Union Asia Enterprise Holdings Limited in April 2016. Union Asia Enterprise Holdings Limited is headquartered in Kwun Tong, Hong Kong.

China Digital Culture (Group) Limited, an investment holding company, engages in licensing and sale of entertainment, and sports and music content in the People's Republic of China. It operates through Entertainment, Sports, and Theme Park segments. The Entertainment segment engages in the business of training, nurturing, and managing eSports teams and eSports broadcasters; distribution of copyright-protected items; production of television drama series and talent management; provision of consultancy services in the cultural industry; and provision of entertainment-related services. The Sports segment is involved in the licensing of professional sports events content; and provision of marketing and promotional services to professional athletes. The Theme park segment operates film-based cultural parks and tourism projects. The company also engages in entertainment project planning and celebrity management activities; production of online streaming content. In addition, it engages in the celebrity and artists training course agency business; selling learning materials; and provision of consulting, and sponsorship and student tuition services. The company was formerly known as China Digital Licensing (Group) Limited. China Digital Culture (Group) Limited was incorporated in 2002 and is headquartered in Hong Kong, Hong Kong.

China Information Technology Development Limited, an investment holding company, operates as an information technology (IT) company in the People's Republic of China, Hong Kong, and Japan. It operates through four segments: Software Development and System Integration, IT Solutions and Maintenance, Money Lending, and Securities Investments. The company develops and sells computer software and hardware; and provides system integration and related support, IT infrastructure solutions and maintenance, money lending, and securities trading services. It also offers office management services; big data application services; and asset acquisition, management, and consultancy services. The company was formerly known as Xteam Software International Limited. China Information Technology Development Limited was founded in 2001 and is based in Kwun Tong, Hong Kong.

Food Idea Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in catering, food business, investments, and money lending activities in Hong Kong. It operates a chain of dessert catering restaurants; produces, sells, and distributes food products to supermarket chains; trades in wine products; and invests in securities, such as equity securities and funds. The company was formerly known as Gayety Holdings Limited and changed its name to Food Idea Holdings Limited in June 2015. Food Idea Holdings Limited was founded in 2006 and is headquartered in Hunghom, Hong Kong.

Shi Shi Services Limited, an investment holding company, provides property management services in the People's Republic of China. It operates in three segments: Provision of Property Management Services, Properties Investment, and Money Lending Business. The company offers security, repair and maintenance, cleaning, finance management, and administrative and legal support services to residential and commercial properties under the Kong Shum brand name. It also invests in properties; and lends money. The company was formerly known as Heng Sheng Holdings Limited and changed its name to Shi Shi Services Limited in October 2018. The company was founded in 1984 and is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong. Shi Shi Services Limited is a subsidiary of Heng Sheng Capital Limited.

Speed Apparel Holding Limited operates as an apparel supply chain management services provider primarily in Japan. The company offers knitwear products comprising women's wear and men's wear; and apparel supply chain management solutions for its customers ranging from fashion trend analysis, product design and development, sourcing and procurement of materials, production management, quality control, and logistics services. It also provides design and customers account services. It serves owners or sourcing agents of apparel retail brands. The company also sells products in Hong Kong, the People's Republic of China, Taiwan, France, the United States, Australia, and South Africa. The company was founded in 1999 and is headquartered in Hung Hom, Hong Kong. Speed Apparel Holding Limited is a subsidiary of Speed Development Co. Ltd.

IR Resources Limited, an investment holding company, primarily engages in forestry and agricultural, financial services, cultural, and logistics businesses in the People's Republic of China, Hong King, and Asian countries. The company operates through four segments: Forestry and Agricultural Business, Financial Services Business, Cultural Business, and Logistics Business. It is involved in timber logging, as well as the plantation and sale of wood and agricultural products. The company also develops rubber plantation for latex production; and trades in timber log. In addition, it provides securities brokerage and trading services; underwriting and placing services; asset management services; loan financing services; and financial information technology services. Further, the company develops and upgrades Chinese cultural related online application. It owns three forests measuring 31,000 hectares in Kratie Province, Cambodia. The company was formerly known as China Asean Resources Limited and changed its name to IR Resources Limited in August 2015. IR Resources Limited is headquartered in Wanchai, Hong Kong.

Jimu Group Limited and its subsidiaries engage in the design, development, sourcing, marketing, and sale of footwear to wholesalers and retailers in Hong Kong and the People's Republic of China. The company operates through two segments, Footwear Business and Loan Facilitation Service. It offers formal and casual footwear for men, women, and children, as well as provides outsource footwear manufacturing services to original equipment manufacturers. The company also exports its footwear products to Australia, the United Kingdom, New Zealand, Belgium, the United Arab Emirates, the United States, Chile, and internationally. In addition, Jimu Group Limited provides loan facilitation services, which assist the qualified borrowers to obtain financing from various financial institutions or investors who have registered with online information intermediary service platforms. Its pre-loan and post-loan facilitation services comprise business consulting and credit assessment services. The company offers its loan facilitation services to individual customers through approximately 40 branch offices in the People's Republic of China. The company was formerly known as Ever Smart International Holdings Limited and changed its name to Jimu Group Limited in February 2018. The company was founded in 2009 and is headquartered in Kowloon, Hong Kong. Jimu Group Limited is a subsidiary of Jimu Group Holdings Limited.

GME Group Holdings Limited provides civil engineering services in Hong Kong. The company provides underground construction services comprising tunnel construction, including excavation, shotcreting, shutter design and fabrication, tunnel lining services, and advanced, slope, and structural works; and utility construction and other services, such as refurbishment of gas pipes and electricity cables. It primarily serves main contractors in public sector infrastructure projects. GME Group Holdings Limited was founded in 1994 and is headquartered in Hong Kong, Hong Kong.

Tianjin TEDA Biomedical Engineering Company Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the research, development, manufacture, and sale of biological compound fertilizer products in the People's Republic of China. The company operates in two segments, Biological Compound Fertilisers Products, and Elderly Care and Health Care Services. Its biological compound fertilizer products are used for the facilitation of balanced growth of grains, fruits, and vegetables. The company is also involved in the provision of integrated elderly and health care, as well as consulting, advisory, and assessment services. In addition, it provides and licenses electroencephalography photography (EEG) detection services; and conducts EEG detection and diagnosis technology services. Further, the company offers research and technology services in the areas of ecological agriculture and forestry technology; and regional soil resources conditioning and remediation, as well as soil environmental quality standards research services. The company has a strategic cooperation agreement with Almage Group. Tianjin TEDA Biomedical Engineering Company Limited was founded in 2000 and is headquartered in Tianjin, the People's Republic of China.
longName: Tianjin TEDA Biomedical Engineering Company Limited

longBusinessSummary: Combest Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides advisory services in Hong Kong, the People's Republic of China, the Cayman Islands, Taiwan, and Europe. The company operates through Money Lending, Advisory Service, and Fund Management Business segments. It offers credit services; consultancy and company secretarial services; and investment management services to investment funds and managed accounts. The company was formerly known as Goldmond Holdings Limited and changed its name to Combest Holdings Limited in June 2010. Combest Holdings Limited was incorporated in 2001 and is headquartered in Hong Kong, Hong Kong.

Hong Wei (Asia) Holdings Company Limited, an investment holding company, manufactures and sells particleboards in the People's Republic of China and other Asian countries. The company's products are primarily used in the production of furniture and fixtures; sport equipment, such as table tennis tables; and decoration and construction materials. It is also involved in the plantation, timber logging, and sale of wood and agricultural products. The company markets and sells its products to home or office furniture manufacturers, sport equipment manufacturers, and wood-based panel processors and traders. Hong Wei (Asia) Holdings Company Limited was incorporated in 2012 and is headquartered in Kowloon, Hong Kong.

Global Token Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the rental of energy-saving air-conditioners in the People's Republic of China, Hong Kong, and Taiwan. The company is also involved in the trading of computer related products; operation of a carbon emission trading platform and related services; money lending business; and securities trading business, which includes brokerage and securities margin financing services. In addition, it offers marketing, administrative, and securities investment services. The company was formerly known as Global Energy Resources International Group Limited and changed its name to Global Token Limited in October 2018. Global Token Limited is headquartered in Tsim Sha Tsui, Hong Kong.

Asia-Pac Financial Investment Company Limited, an investment holding company, provides integrated professional services to public and private companies, and individual investors primarily in Hong Kong and the People's Republic of China. It operates through four segments: Asset Advisory Services and Asset Appraisal, Corporate Services and Consultancy, Media Advertising, and Financial Services. The Asset Advisory Services and Asset Appraisal segment offers real estate and fixed asset appraisal; mineral property appraisal; business and intangible asset valuation; financial instrument and derivative valuation; and advisory services, such as investments or investors identification, due diligence and underlying assets evaluation, and procedural and strategic business advices. The Corporate Services and Consultancy segment provides secretarial services, human resource management and other administrative services, accounting and tax services, corporate communication and marketing services, and management consultancy services, as well as corporate governance, internal control, and enterprise risk management services. The Media Advertising segment offers media advertising business services through in-elevator poster frames network and liquid-crystal displays network inside elevators or lobbies of middle to high-end residential community. The Financial Services segment provides financial credit services, such as personal loans, commercial loans, and mortgages to individuals and corporations; and offers securities broking, trading, placing, and underwriting services. The company also sub-leases office. Asia-Pac Financial Investment Company Limited was incorporated in 2010 and is headquartered in Wanchai, Hong Kong.

L & A International Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, manufactures and sells cashmere garments and other apparel products in Hong Kong, the United States, Europe, and China. It operates through four segments: OEM Business, Retail Business, Money Lending, and Wholesaling Business. The OEM Business segment engages in the design and development, raw material sourcing and procurement, and manufacturing and product quality control management activities. This segment also produces pure and blended cashmere products, as well as garments using merino wool, linen, and cotton for apparel brand owners or chain department stores. The Retail Business segment is involved in designing, procuring, manufacturing, marketing, and retailing cashmere and other apparel, as well as accessories under the Casimira trademark. The Money Lending segment provides loan and other financial services. The Wholesaling Business segment engages in wholesaling baby products and seafood. The company also engages in organizing talks and seminars; and the securities investment business. L & A International Holdings Limited was founded in 2001 and is headquartered in Kowloon, Hong Kong.

Great Water Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides engineering services for the wastewater and drinking water treatment facilities in the People's Republic of China. It operates through five segments: Engineering, Procurement and Construction Projects; Construction Projects; Equipment Projects; Service Concession Arrangement; and Others. The company designs, procures, and constructs water or wastewater treatment facilities; and other environmental protection projects, such as soil remediation project and flue gas treatment project. It also engages in the procurement of materials, equipment, and machinery; and installation, testing, and commissioning of the equipment and machinery for the treatment facilities, as well as provides technical consulting services. In addition, the company is involved in the design, construction, and sale of equipment for wastewater projects, as well as offers operation and maintenance services for water or wastewater treatment facilities. Further, it constructs, maintains, restores, and operates sludge treatment facilities and sludge stations. The company was formerly known as Great Water EP Holdings Limited and changed its name to Great Water Holdings Limited in November 2015. Great Water Holdings Limited was founded in 2001 and is headquartered in Guangzhou, the People's Republic of China.

Loto Interactive Limited, an investment holding company, provides lottery-related technologies, systems and solutions to two state-run lottery operators in the People's Republic of China. It operates through three segments: Big Data Centre Services, Online Game Business, and Lottery Business. The company distributes online mobile games; and lottery terminals and parts for the CSLA, as well as provides game upgrading technology and system maintenance services. It also provides data analysis, storage, and ancillary administrative and consulting services. The company was formerly known as MelcoLot Limited and changed its name to Loto Interactive Limited in September 2017. Loto Interactive Limited is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong.

China Wan Tong Yuan (Holdings) Limited, an investment holding company, provides burial services in the People's Republic of China. The company sells burial plots and provides cemetery maintenance services. It also offers other burial-related services, such as the organization and conducting of interment rituals; the design, construction, and landscaping of the burial plots; and the engraving of inscriptions and ceramic photographs on the headstones. The company was founded in 2007 and is headquartered in Langfang, the People's Republic of China. China Wan Tong Yuan (Holdings) Limited is a subsidiary of Tai Shing International Investment Company Limited.

Sau San Tong Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the distribution and sale of cosmetic and skin care products. It also provides beauty and slimming services, such as whole and partial body slimming, weight management, body treatment, and facial treatment services through its slimming centers, which operate under the Sau San Tong and IPRO brands. In addition, the company is involved in the sale of other health and beauty products; property holding; money lending; and investment in securities. Further, it provides management consultancy, advertising agency, and franchise services; and a proprietary Internet platform to promote and sell slimming beauty and health related services and products. The company operates 9 beauty and slimming centers comprising 5 centers in Hong Kong; 1 in Macau; and 3 in Mainland China, including 1 in Beijing, 1 in shanghai, and 1 in Shenzhen. Sau San Tong Holdings Limited was founded in 2000 and is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong.

PPS International (Holdings) Limited, an investment holding company, primarily provides environmental services in Hong Kong and the People's Republic of China. It operates through Environmental and Cleaning, Money Lending, and Investments segments. The company offers public area and office cleaning services, such as cleaning of public areas, carpets, floors, toilets, changing rooms, lifts, and escalators; and emptying of garbage bins at commercial buildings and their tenants, residential complexes, shopping arcades, and hotels, as well as at public transport facilities, such as airports, ferries, ferry terminals, and cargo and logistics centers and depots. It also provides overnight kitchen cleaning services primarily at private clubs and hotels; external wall and window cleaning services; stone floor maintenance and restoration services; pest control and fumigation services; and waste management and disposal solutions, such as collection, transportation, and disposal of household waste, construction waste, and trade waste, as well as sells recyclable waste, such as paper, metal, and plastic waste. In addition, the company provides housekeeping services at local boutique hotels, hostels, and serviced apartments; secure and confidential waste destruction services for commercial clients; sanitation solutions for yacht; and cleaning and waste management solutions for renovated apartments. Further, it engages in provision of airline catering support services; and money lending and financial assets investment businesses. PPS International (Holdings) Limited was founded in 1978 and is headquartered in North Point, Hong Kong.

Inno-Tech Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides advertising services in the People's Republic of China. It operates through Outdoor Advertising; Advertisements and Event Management Services; Money Lending; Advertising on Shared Paper Towel; and Sales and Distribution of Seafood segments. The company engages in the design, production, and publication of outdoor advertisements on buses and bus stations; and provision of advertisements on billboards and televisions, as well as event management, marketing, marketing consultancy, and money lending services. In addition, it offers advertising on shared paper towels and tissue boxes. Further, the company sells and distributes seafood, such as live clam and lobster. Inno-Tech Holdings Limited was incorporated in 2001 and is headquartered in Mongkok, Hong Kong.

Kaisun Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the mining, exploitation, processing, production, and sale of coal. It operates through eight segments: Production and Exploitation of Coal in Tajikistan, Production and Exploitation of Coal in Xinjiang, Provision of Supply Chain Management Services for Mineral Business, Trading Securities, Mining and Metallurgical Machineries Production in Shandong, Organising eSports Event, Corporate Services Business, and Media Services. The company mines for thermal coal, and anthracite and bituminous coal. It also provides supply chain management services for the mineral business; produces mining and metallurgical machineries; trades in securities; and manufactures coal mining related equipment. In addition, the company engages in the provision of corporate, consulting, project investment, advertising and public relationship event, media, and trust and trustee services; and e-commerce, e-sport, and financial lease and general trading businesses. It has operations in Hong Kong, rest of the People's Republic of China, Taiwan, Tajikistan, Malaysia, Vietnam, Macau, and internationally. The company was formerly known as Kaisun Energy Group Limited and changed its name to Kaisun Holdings Limited in July 2018. Kaisun Holdings Limited was incorporated in 2002 and is headquartered in Wong Chuk Hang, Hong Kong.

Shanghai Jiaoda Withub Information Industrial Company Limited develops and provides business application solutions primarily in the People's Republic of China. The company operates through two segments, Business Application Project and Application Software; and Sales of Products. It develops and provides business application solutions, which include business solutions and application software, as well as installation and maintenance of Internet and data security products. The company also sells computer hardware and software products, electronic products, and accessories. Shanghai Jiaoda Withub Information Industrial Company Limited was founded in 1998 and is based in Wanchai, Hong Kong.
longName: Shanghai Jiaoda Withub Information Industrial Company Limited

longBusinessSummary: Shentong Robot Education Group Company Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the robotics education in the People's Republic of China. It provides promotion, sales, and management services for an electronic smart card under the Designated Shentong Card name. The company also engages in organizing and hosting of China Robot Competition; and training business. In addition, it is involved in the provision of robot related consultancy services. The company was formerly known as China Communication Telecom Services Company Limited and changed its name to Shentong Robot Education Group Company Limited in September 2016. Shentong Robot Education Group Company Limited is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong.
longName: Shentong Robot Education Group Company Limited

longBusinessSummary: Chong Sing Holdings FinTech Group Limited, an investment holding company, provides online financial services to small and medium-sized enterprises, merchants, and individuals through Internet and mobile solutions.
